(753, 'US8386667', 'Existing methods used two timers for each data fragment during transmission, and used purge timers during reception of fragments, thus requiring a large number of timers and additional OS resources such as memory/processing time to manage the timers.', 'The invention provides a method for management of transmitted and/or received fragments, wherein the method minimizes the number of timers needed for management of data fragments, and hence lowers the memory and operating requirements on the operating system in managing the data fragments. The method uses a single timer for a connection between the receiver and the transmitter, wherein the timer sequentially processes fragments and, for each fragment, runs until processing of the fragment is terminated by either timing out of the timer or receipt of an acknowledgement. The same single timer is then reassigned to the next subsequent data fragment', 'Management of transmitted or received data fragments in protocols such as WiMax and LTE.', 'Products and systems complying with LTE, including:<br />\n Mobile Stations<br />\nCell Phones<br />\nPCMCIA Card<br />\nUSB Dongle<br />\nWireless Modules/ Chips<br />\nWireless NIC <br />\n  Wireless Sensors <br />\n  NFC Devices<br />\n  Wireless Adapter<br />\n  Personal Navigation Devices<br />\n  Consumer Appliances<br />\n Intermediate Devices:<br />\n Access Nodes, <br />\n Modems, <br />\n Routers, <br />\n Cellular Repeaters, <br />\n Customer Premise Equipments (CPE), <br />\n Internet Hotspots:BACK-END DEVICES<br />\n  Remote Radio Unit (RRU)<br />\n  Base Transceiver System (BTS)<br />\n  Base Station Controller (BSC)<br />\n  Mobile Switching Center (MSC)<br />\n  Radio Network Controller (RNC)<br />\n  Gateway Node<br />\n  Wireless Backhaul Mobile Switching Center (MSC)<br />\n  Radio Network Controller (RNC)<br />\n  Gateway Node<br />\n  Wireless Backhaul', 'Broadcom<br />\n Qualcomm<br />\n Fujitsu<br />\n Motorola<br />\n ZTE<br />\n Erricsson