(872, 'US7076037B1', 'Sources of telephone leads (a phone call coming from a potential customer interested in a product or a service) are interested in maximizing their revenues from selling such telephone leads. The value of leads are perceived differently in eyes of different marketers (providers of services or products), each of which is interested to acquire a lead at a different price. Moreover, since a telephone lead can be sold only once, selling a lead to a random interested marketer would not yield maximum revenues to the leads source.', 'This invention describes a mechanism that allows a telephone lead source to sell the lead to the marketer who is willing to pay the highest price for the lead. Due to the "real time" nature of a telephone call, the solution provided here routs customers'' calls received by the lead source to one out of many interested marketers based on the price the marketers are interested to pay for the lead.\r\nThe invention provides a mechanism that allows marketers to bid against one another for a per-call charge. When a lead source receives a telephone call from a customer the telephone call is routed to the highest bidder.\r\nIn case the highest bidder does not answer the call within a predetermined number of rings, the call is re-routed to the next highest bidder. \r\nThe service provider who answers the call is charged \r\nThe invention also includes a mechanism that takes into consideration the geographic location of the customer in determining to which marketer to rout the telephone lead.', 'Advertising Systems/Solutions<br/>Toll-Free Call Routing<br/>Online Search Portals<br/>Vanity Numbers - Call Routing<br/>', '', '', '<a data-mainlink="https://www.youtube.com/user/RingRouter" href="https://browshot.com/screenshot/image/41949227?key=oUnAlHUsWOlbzz51xFahrTguIE7I6JQN&scale=1">Ring Router - Ring Router</a><br/><a data-mainlink="http://www.rextopia.com/rex_connect.php" href="https://browshot.com/screenshot/image/41949250?key=oUn