(873, 'US7953416B2', 'An advertiser  sells leads to service providers to make revenue. While selling a lead, in order to maximize revenues, the advertiser must select a service provider who values the lead more than the other similar service providers. The value may be determined by the price the service provider is willing to pay for the lead.\r\n\r\nTherefore, there is a need for a process using which the advertiser is able to sell to the service provider willing to pay the highest price for the lead. Thereby, extracting the maximum monetary value out of the lead.\r\n\r\nFurther, in case the service provider being offered the lead (telephone call) does not respond in time, the advertiser may lose the lead and the associated monetary value. Therefore, there is a need of a mechanism that enables the advertiser to offer the same lead to another service provider. ', 'The present invention describes a mechanism that enables an advertiser to extract the maximum monetary value out of selling a lead. The lead may in the form of a telephone call or an electronic message.\r\n\r\nThe mechanism allows service providers to bid against each other on  a per-contact charge. On receiving the lead from a customer, the advertiser routes the lead to the highest bidder. In case the highest bidder does not respond to the lead, the advertiser reroutes the lead to the next highest bidder.\r\n\r\nA service provider, who responds to the lead, is charged based on the per-contact bid placed by the service provider. This way, the advertiser sells the lead to the service provider who is willing to pay the most for the lead.\r\n\r\nFurther, the mechanism also enables the advertiser to consider the geographic location of the customer while routing the lead to the service providers.', 'Advertising Systems/Solutions<br/>Toll-Free Call Routing<br/>Online Search Portals<br/>Vanity Numbers - Call Routing<br/>', '', '', '<a data-mainlink="https://www.youtube.com/user/RingRouter" href="https://browshot