 a Participant, a Regular Licensee, or Late (Risk Averse) Licensee.&nbsp;</div><div style="outline: 0px; line-height: 18.5714px;"><br></div><div style="line-height: 18.5714px;">The third document is a draft of the Strategic License Agreement (SLA) in case you would like to acquire from SynPat the rights to license (and enforce this patent portfolio on) a designated third party, perhaps one of your competitors. While the price of a regular non-exclusive license under the PLA changes from Cost Price to Regular Price and then to Validated Price, the price of Strategic License is always a Regular Price regardless of the time it is purchased.</div><div style="line-height: 18.5714px;"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><br></span></div><div style="line-height: 18.5714px;"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">The PPP is a long document that describes the entire program including the different mechanisms that determine the pricing, timing, and procedure.&nbsp;</span></div><div style="line-height: 18.5714px;"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><br></span></div><div style="line-height: 18.5714px;"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">The last document - and the most important - is your Request to Participate (RTP). When you decide that you wish to participate in the syndication to fund the acquisition of this patent portfolio - whether because you want a non-exclusive license, a strategic license, or simply for the great ROI expected for Participants, go ahead and download this two-page form, fill in the maximum amount you would like to contribute to the syndicate and send it to us using the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page. Please note that your participation fee will be determined according to the formula: Seller''s Asking Price / Number of Participants. &nbsp;The maximum amount that you state on your RTP is only an indication of your intention used for SynPat to figure out whether or not it has requests from potential participants that cumulatively suffice to close the syndicate. At the end, all Participants will pay the same - according to the above simple formula.</span><div><br></div><div>All the documents can be downloaded and revised by our customers. It''s like when you enter a department store to buy a suit and you find the one you like at the right shape and size, still there are always a few minor modifications to be made so the suit will fits you perfectly. The same here: although SynPat''s licenses are standard, still we always allow our customers to make those few minor modifications as to make their licenses fit them perfectly. Feel free to review and download the documents below and if you like to add your minor modifications please do so and upload your files back to SynPat. We will review your revisions and get back to you swiftly.</div></div>', '', '', '', '', 1, 'The Syndication stage of this portfolio has completed. At this time, you may acquire a Regular License', 'The Syndication stage for this portfolio is still open, and you may acquire a license as a Participant. Regular Licenses will be available upon a successful syndication.', 'Risk Averse Licenses will be available upon completion of both the Syndication and the Regular Licensing stages.', '<p>Thank you for your interest in participating in this syndicate. Please feel free to contact me with any questions. As you may know, the participation fee is calculated by dividing the Seller''s Upfront Price by the number of Participants. Please download the Request to Participate from the Documents tab, fill it out and submit it to SynPat, using this form.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Regular License under this portfoio. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent Licensee Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and submit it to SynPat using this form. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 50% higher than the price each Participant paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired (as a Strategic License) by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Validated License under this patent portfoio. We call it a Validated License because so many other licensees have validated this patent portfolio since it was introduced by SynPat. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent License Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and upload it using the button below. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 100% higher than the amount each Regular Licensee paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', 0, NULL, '12345', '', 'admin@123', '', '12345', NULL, '', '12345', NULL, '12345', '12345', '', '12345', '', '12345', '', 'admin@123'),
(119, '', 'B3D_Inc.', 0, '', 'B3D Inc.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '12345', '12345', 0, '12345', '', '1.3', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<blockquote>\n<h4>Introduction:</h4>\n<p>This patent portofolio comprises of 21 US granted patents across 5 families related to Interactive Media and Questionnaire systems, and 13 pending patent applications. There are no foreign counterparts in these patent families.</p>\n<p>The technology portfolio comprises of fundamental patents in the following technology areas: Interactive Media Creation &amp; Distribution specifically content delivery for portable wireless devices such as mobile phones, tablet pcâ€™s (Dynamic/Interactive contents such as Mobile Questionnaire Systems, Guided Activities &amp; Advertisements, Local Sharing of Content by mobile devices, and Color detection in mobile devices)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The earliest priority date in the poraolio is November 22, 2006.</li>\n<li>Encumbrances: None. No buyer restrictions.</li>\n<li class="ms-hover">Sell-side Adviser: ICEBERGPrice expectation: US $3m.</li>\n<li class="ms-hover">Evidence of Use analysis suggesting infringement by Google, Apple, SurveyMonkey and SurveyMini.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Legal Discussion:</h4>\n</blockquote>', '<blockquote>\n<p>You may use this Program Simulator to figure out whether to acquire a license under this patent portfolio, and if so, at which stage of the Program. If you decide to particpate in the Syndicae, the Simulator may assit you in figuring out what amout to state in your Request to Participate.</p>\n<p>The table on the left had side consists of the list of companies that were invited to participate in the Syndicate. Using the Stage button next to each company''s name, you can create different scenarios: which companies with participate in the Syndicate to fund the acqusition, which companies will buy licenses as Regular Licensees, and which companies will wait and acquire licenses as Risk Averse Licenses.</p>\n<p>Keep in mind these basic principles:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class="ms-hover">Participants'' license fee is the "cost price", which is simply the Seller''s asking price divided by the number of participants. Since participants are entitled to one third of any license fees received from licensees who don''t participate in the syndicate, the "net cost" for participants is the cost price minus the each participant''s share in the future revenues.</li>\n<li>Regular licensees - companies that decide to acquire a license during the first 4 months after the close of the syndicate and the acquisition of the patents pay regular price, which is 50% above the cost price.</li>\n<li>Validated Prices are the price a company will pay if acquires the license at any time after the first 4 months. The validated price is twice the regular price.</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>', '<p>The following patent purchase agreement is the one executed between the patent seller and SynPat.</p>', '<p>The following document is an offer to contract under a patent license agreement, conditioned upon a successful syndication. SynPat is bound by the terms of the executed offer, and licensees may simply download the offer and accept it.</p>', '<p>In order to participate in this syndicate, you must download the Request to Participate form below fill it in with: 1. the maximum amount that you are willing to contribute into the syndicate. 2. whether you would like to acquire SynPat''s rights to license a third party, and the name of the designated party. Receiving the maximum amount that you would be willing to pay to participate would allow SynPat to determine whether the Seller''s asking price could be raised and the syndicate could be close. It is essential that you send your indication of interest to participate as soon as possible, mainly because the syndicate could close before you do that, but also because another participant might ask to acquire your license. If that happens before you send y