(124, '', 'Gestion_Proche', 13907043, 'dchev@outlook.com', 'Gestion Proche', '<p>1. Locate and select your company''s name from the list of invitees.</p>\r\n<p>2. Set the stages at which other companies might join the Progam,&nbsp;either as a Participant, a Regular Licensee, or a Late Licensee.</p>\r\n<p>3. Create different scenarios and see how each affects the cost of your license.</p>\r\n<p>4. Decide whether you would like to joint the Program and at which stage.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B61I0m5ybHrFc0V3M0VROHk5ekU/view?usp=drivesdk', '', '', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1yWPVuGkg_Zr2OuO7UjkcUHLkzGIMnumdAq6ZFnrvtCA/edit?usp=drivesdk', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1HdS8oHxO9_KkJr6SOmJYTcdKD2Cots5Xiy67qw5v1bs/edit?usp=drivesdk', '', '', '', '<iframe src="http://claimcharts.info/index.php/component/survey/?tmpl=component&task=customer.generateClientRequest&client_id=Gestion&pr=2" width="100%" height="680" frameborder="0" scrolling="yes"></iframe>', '<iframe src="http://claimcharts.info/index.php/component/survey/?tmpl=component&task=customer.generateClientRequest&client_id=Gestion&pr=1" width="100%" height="680" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe>', '', '12345', 'd4n13l', 0, '12345', '03/24/2016', '0.6', '', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/DigitralLumens2.jpg', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/EatonMetalux.jpg', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/HubbellWihubb.jpg', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/Philips2.jpg', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/Lusio.jpg', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/Flextronics.jpg', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/GEABR1.jpg', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/Osram.jpg', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/LeoLed.jpg', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/Encelium.png', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/cooperlighting-greengate-banner.jpg', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/Lithonia Lighting.jpg', '<div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">SynPat decided to acquire this patent portfolio since it covers many potential licensees who could benefit from obtaining licenses that are unavailable otherwise. This portfolio is directed to LED lighting systems, and in particular to techniques for delivering an LED lighting system that maintains appropriate lighting levels given ambient lighting conditions (also referred to as a daylight harvesting control system).</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">Companies that provide LED light controlling systems, light controlling software, and/or related hardware may be interested in this portfolio.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">The priority date of December 2000 is on the cusp of sharply increased development activity in the field of intelligent LED lighting systems. &nbsp;The portfolio is comprised of three assets: &nbsp;one US granted patent, one granted German patent, and one Canadian patent application.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">The expected number of licensees as they spread along the three segments of the market together with the information provided in this docket support a rational decision to participate in the effort to crowdfund the acquisition of this portfolio.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">So long as SynPat holds a portfolio of patents, any operating company may submit to SynPat a request to acquire from SynPat either a Defensive License, a Strategic License, or both.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">A Defensive License is a paid up nonexclusive license under the acquired patent portfolio.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">A Strategic License provides is buyer the right to license any other operating company of its choice (â€œDesignated Third Partyâ€).&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">A request to acquire a license is always subject to availability. &nbsp;For example, a request by Company A to acquire a Strategic License that would allow it to exclusively license Company B must arrive to SynPat before a similar request from Company C, or a request from Company B to acquire a Defensive License is received by SynPat. Also, a request by Company B to acquire a Defensive License must arrive to SynPat before a request from Company A to acquire a Strategic License, which would allow it to exclusively license Company B, is received by SynPat.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">In guiding its actions, SynPat will use the date and time of actual receipt of any request, and unless the date and time of the request to acquire the right to license a Designated Third Party can be clearly shown to have been received by SynPat prior to a request for a Defensive License by the Designated Third Party, SynPat will honor the request of the Designated Third Party.</span></div><div style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></div></div>', '<div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">The simulator below is aimed to assist you in figuring out at which of the three stages to acquire your license, once you decided to acquire one. &nbsp;It allows you to simulate scenarios under which several companies purchases licenses by participating in the crowdfunding syndicate, while others acquire their licenses later on as Regular Licensees, and some very conservative ones obtain their licenses as Late Licensees at any time after the Regular Licensing period.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div>Price differences:</div><div><ol><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Participants</span> pay a Cost Price, which is simply the Seller''s upfront price divided by the number of participants (SUP/NoP). Since Participants are entitled to receive from SynPat an equal share of 1/3 of all license fees received from licensees who did participate in the syndicate, i.e. from Regular Licensees, and Late Licensees, the "net cost" for each Participant is equal to the Cost Price minus its share in the future sales of licenses.</span></span></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Regular Licensees</span> - companies that decide to acquire a license during the first 4 months after the close of the syndicate - pay a Regular Price, which is equal to 1.5 x Cost Price.</span></span></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Late Licensees</span> pay a Validated Price - the price a company will pay if acquires the license at any time after the 4 months Regular Licensing period. The Validated price is equal to 2 x Regular Price.</span></span></li></ol></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">The table on the left hand side includes the list of companies that were invited to participate in the Syndicate and to acquire licenses at any later time. Using the Stage button next to each company''s name, you can create different scenarios and determine which companies will participate in the Syndicate, those who will buy licenses as Regular Licensees, and the laggards who will wait and acquire licenses only after many others will have bought the same licenses.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">The three middle tables represent the three stages: Syndicate Participation, Regular Licensing, and Late Licensing, and will include the company names according to your selections and your estimated scenarios.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">The first thing to begin with is to select the radio button next to your company''s name. Doing so will send your company to the first table of Participants. You can move it to different stages by changing the Select Stage button next to your company name.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">Next, use the Select Stage buttons next to the companies you believe will buy a license to determine at which stage each will acquire its license. &nbsp;We believe that the more conservative a company is, the later it will acquire its license. The main reason for that could be the time it takes for such companies to assess the opportunity, decide, and react. Another reason could be the preferences of such companies to allow other companies to validate the quality of the license and the price, taking into consideration that higher price they would pay reflects the confidence they gain.</span></div>', '<p>The following patent purchase agreement is the one executed between the patent seller and SynPat.</p>', '<p>The following document is an offer to contract under a patent license agreement, conditioned upon a successful syndication. SynPat is bound by the terms of the executed offer, and licensees may simply download the offer and accept it.</p>', '<p>In order to participate in this syndicate, you must download the Request to Participate form below fill it in with: 1. the maximum amount that you are willing to contribute into the syndicate. 2. whether you would like to acquire SynPat''s rights to license a third party, and the name of the designated party. Receiving the maximum amount that you would be willing to pay to participate would allow SynPat to determine whether the Seller''s asking price could be raised and the syndicate could be close. It is essential that you send your indication of interest to participate as soon as possible, mainly because the syndicate could close before you do that, but also because another participant might ask to acquire your license. If that happens before you send your request to participate, SynPat Program - Process and Procedure mandates that your license to be sold to that requesting participants.</p>', '<p>The following information was diligently collected and prepared in effort to enable prospect Participants and Licensees to learn the scope of the inventions included in this portfolio, based on which make informed decisions whether or not to join this syndicate or to buy licenses at later times. We made special efforts to illustrate selected claims, element by element, which you can find under the Illustrations tab. Each mouse click will reveal additional claim element together with a corresponding illustration. This process is aimed to assist in quickly grasping the full scope of the entire claim as a whole. Please feel free to send us any inquiries relating the information provided here.</p>', '<p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">This page is dedicated to demonstrating the impact of this patent portfolio. Impact is associated with the likelihood of a portfolio to generate a large amounts of license fees, which generally happens where the patents cover significant sources of revenues of large number of potential licensees. To learn about the impact of this patent portfolio we provided the following:</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Forward Citations:</span>&nbsp;Since both the applicant and the patent examiner must find and cite documents that may anticipate a claimed invention, the number of forward citations a patent receives, the citing entities, and the pattern of citing may point on the patent''s acknowledgement by others and sometimes even on its significance and relevance to others'' technologies.</span><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ''Open Sans'', arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px;">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ''Open Sans'', arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Claim Charts:</span>&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 20.8px;">SynPat posted an order on ClaimCharts.info - a third party application - to produce claim charts reports. Via this online platform, subject matter experts were invited to study and prepare reports showing evidence of use, addressing each and every element of select claims from this portfolio. Posting of reports under the Claim Charts section is done automatically. Click on the patent(claim) number to see whether claim charts reports were submitted. If there are any, you may click the BUY button and purchase the reports using Paypal payment directly to the author of the report - the subject matter expert person or firm who prepared it. The prices and content of such reports are not the responsibility of SynPat.</span></p><p><span style="line-height: 20.8px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Comparables:</span>&nbsp;Although SynPat offers licenses at three fixed prices: Cost Price = SUP/NoP, Regular Price = 1.5 x Cost Price, and Validated Price = 2 x Regular Price, in order to assist our customers in making informed decisions and properly evaluate this opportunity, it is useful to take into consideration alternative pricing. This section contains documents that can teach about the reasonable royalty rates that are relevant to this patent portfolio, as well as a sample of patent license agreements covering technologies with characteristics that are similar to the subject patents.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Royalty Rate Study:</span>&nbsp;Since patent licensing markets are known to be highly inefficient, and market transaction data is subject to significant error, the license fee appraisal process generally relies on multiple simultaneous approaches to value, with a&nbsp;judgmental&nbsp;reconciliation as the final step to arrive at the appraiser''s opinion. Thus, an Expert Royalty Rate Study was conducted specifically for this portfolio in an effort to identify the applicable range of&nbsp;reasonable royalty rates.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">License Fee Estimator:</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">&nbsp;After reviewing the&nbsp;comparables&nbsp;and studying the Expert Royalty Rate Study, you''ll be able to effectively use the License Fee Estimator to quickly and simply estimate your specific alternative cost of a license under&nbsp;this portfolio following these steps:</span></p><p></p><ol style="line-height: 18.5714px;"><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Apply your judgement to figure out the Maximum Royalty Rate and the Minimum Royalty Rate that could be applied to this portfolio, and plug them in the Estimator to calculate the&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: underline;">average</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">&nbsp;royalty rate.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Use the handle bar to adjust the average royalty rate in order to take into consideration and reflect specific circumstances that require a higher or lower rate, in order to obtain the&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: underline;">reasonable</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">&nbsp;royalty rate.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Enter your average addressable sales that might be found covered by the parent portfolio.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Enter the relevant number of years of an applicable license.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Calculate your expected alternative license fee.</span></li></ol>', '<p>The following content is aimed to demonstrate the quality of this portfolio. We use the term quality to relate to the likelihood of a licensing campaign to sustain challenges. The materials below contains information on the existence of licenses granted under this portfolio, and if there are any - to the nature of such licenses. Most of the information in this page is not publicly available, and therefore was provided by the seller. This page also contains information about the chain of title, and addresses irregularities or missing items that might make the potentially transferred title questionable or unclear. In some cases, when needed, we provided the agreements showing assignments along the life of the patents. We also included declarations and information by the seller with regard to the involvement and rights of third parties such as universities and governmental agencies that might pose challenges and hardship in future licensing. Involvement of the inventors or the seller in industry standard activities and the existence of potential commitments to different SSO to FRAND terms licensing is also addressed. Next are data relating to collateral by creditors and other third parties that might encumber the portfolio and the ability to license it. We also included reports from patent offices relating to payment of maintenance fees, and other activities that might affect a the licensing power. Information on backward citations is provided as well, and is aimed to show whether and to what extent the inventor and examiner addressed prior arts.</p><p><br></p><p>SynPat posted an order on ClaimCharts.info - a third party application - to produce prior art reports. Via this online platform, subject matter experts were invited to study and prepare reports showing invalidating prior art, addressing each and every element of select claims from this portfolio. Posting of reports under the Prior Art section is done automatically. Click on the patent(claim) number to see whether prior art reports were submitted. If there are any, you may click the BUY button and purchase the reports using Paypal payment directly to the author of the report - the subject matter expert person or firm who prepared it. The prices and content of such reports are not the responsibility of SynPat.</p>', '<p>The following content is imported from ClaimCharts.info, a free platform that facilitates crowdsourcing of patent infringement and prior art research. Every uploaded claim is broken into its elements and sent to a network of independent subject matter experts who conduct their researches to find evidence that each of the claim elements is either implemented (ClaimChart Report) or anticipated (PriorArt Report). Interested parties may acquire the reports directly from the experts at prices set by the experts.</p>', '<p>This is the text for program</p>', '<div style="line-height: 18.5714px;"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">The Syndication Process is explained and illustrated below:</span><br></div><div style="line-height: 18.5714px;"><ol><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">The syndication process begins with the execution of a Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) between a patent seller and SynPat, who is purchasing the patents. The PPA defines the main four items: 1) the list of patents to be acquired by SynPat, 2) the Sellerâ€™s Upfront Price (SUP), 3) the deadline for the closing, which is generally 100 days, and 4) SynPat''s rights to grant licenses upon noticing the Seller of a successful syndicate, before any payments are made by any party.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">SynPat begins an extensive due diligence resulting with the invitation of relevant operating companies to participate in crowdfunding the SUP. The invitations to participate include a copy of the PPA, a draft Patent License Agreement (PLA) under which SynPat will grant the non-exclusive licenses under the acquired patent portfolio, a draft Strategic License that would allow interested customers to exclusively license designated companies of its choice (provided such companies have not yet purchased licenses), a Request to Participate form for interested customers to submit to SynPat their commitments to participate in the syndicate, and finally, a copy of the program terms - a document that explains the SynPat licensing stages.&nbsp;</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Companies that wish to participate in the syndicate must send to SynPat a Request to Participate, stating the maximum license fee they commit to pay. Clicking the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page would allow you to submit your executed Request to Participate together with any comments, requests, or instructions to SynPat. Upon doing that, you''ll receive an immediate confirmation on receiving your request. Please keep in mind that your participation is secured and you will be considered a participant when SynPat receives commitments from interested companies, sufficient to equally crowdfund the SUP, and your committed amount is equal or greater than the SUP divided by the number of participating companies (NoP).</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Upon receiving Requests to Participate from interested companies, sufficient to equally crowdfund the SUP, SynPat will notify the Seller of the successful syndicate formation. The notice to Seller effectuates the licenses to all the participants. Note that licenses to participants become effective before the fee is paid by them.&nbsp;</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Next, SynPat sends to all participants a Payment Notice stating the exact participation fee to be paid (= SUP/NoP).</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Participants then counter execute the License Agreement, and pay their participation fee within seven calendar days. Please note that payments are to be made directly to the Sellerâ€™s bank account, as stated in the PPA and the PLA.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Upon full payment of the SUP to the Seller, the title to the acquired patents is assigned to SynPat. Note that a failure to pay a participation fee by any participant does not affect the validity of your licenses. Rest assured that your license is in full effect upon your receiving a Payment Notice from SynPat.</span></li></ol></div>', '<p>This is damage text1.</p>', '', '', 'Uzi Aloush', 'uzi@synpat.com', '415-805-8813', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/Copy of UziAloush.jpg', '', '', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ZRRDNAAuXIJCsu3K2m8SisgvCAF7157h_6lTyrJv9S4/edit?usp=drivesdk', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Y8hYMfV6E0yd3v7Eq34rPZd3y1pqjdaM4ksCiYrnYWA/edit?usp=drivesdk', '<div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;">This page contains the following documents and functionalities:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><span style="transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">PURCHASE AGREEMENT</span>&nbsp;- a copy of the actual Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) as executed between the seller of this patent portfolio and SynPat as a buyer. This agreement is subject to confidentiality terms, and the parties agreed to expose the agreement to you as a potential Participant or a Licensee, but not to others. Please respect the parties'' agreement and kindly refrain from disclosing it to third parties.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">NON-EXCLUSIVE LICENSE</span>&nbsp;- a draft of SynPat standard Patent License Agreement. This agreement is applicable to all licensees whether they acquire their licenses as Participants, Regular Licensees, or Late Licensees. The difference is in the prices paid in exchange for the non-exclusive license. Participants pay the Cost Price = SUP/NoP and are entitled&nbsp;to receive from SynPat an equal share of 1/3 of all license fees received from licensees who did participate in the syndicate. Regular Licensees'' pay the Regular Price = 1.5 x Cost Price, and Late Licensees pay the Validated Price - 2 x Regular Price.</span></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">STRATEGIC LICENSE</span>&nbsp;- a draft of SynPat standard Strategic License Agreement (SLA) in case you would like to acquire from SynPat the rights to license (and enforce this patent portfolio on) a designated third party, perhaps one of your competitors. While the price of a regular non-exclusive license under the PLA changes from Cost Price to Regular Price and then to Validated Price, the price of Strategic License is always a Regular Price regardless of the time it is purchased.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">REQUEST TO PARTICIPATE</span>&nbsp;- the Request to Participate (RTP) form is used to by companies to inform SynPat about their intention to participate in the syndicate to crowdfund the SUP. To use this form, download and print it, fill it in and execute it, then use the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page to upload and submit it to SynPat. Please note that your participation fee will be determined according to the formula: Seller''s Asking Price / Number of Participants. &nbsp;The maximum amount that you state on your RTP is for SynPat to figure out whether your request is suffice for participation taking into consideration the requsts submitted by others. Ultimately, you, like all all other Participants will pay the same amount: Cost Price = SUP/NoP.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">PROGRAM</span>&nbsp;- The SynPat Program Procedure and Policies (PPP) describes in details the unique licensing approach offered by SynPat.</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><br></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 21.4286px;"><span style="color: inherit; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">DOWNLOAD / UPLOAD</span>&nbsp;- From this page customers can download the above documents. If you would like to suggest revisions to the language of any of the documents you may do so by downloading them, making your tracked edits and submitting them back to SynPat using the form on this page.</span></div>', '', '', '', '', 1, 'The Syndication stage of this portfolio has completed. At this time, you may acquire a Regular License', 'The Syndication stage for this portfolio is still open, and you may acquire a license as a Participant. Regular Licenses will be available upon a successful syndication.', 'Risk Averse Licenses will be available upon completion of both the Syndication and the Regular Licensing stages.', '<p>Thank you for your interest in participating in this syndicate. Please feel free to contact me with any questions. As you may know, the participation fee is calculated by dividing the Seller''s Upfront Price by the number of Participants. Please download the Request to Participate from the Documents tab, fill it out and submit it to SynPat, using this form.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Regular License under this portfoio. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent Licensee Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and submit it to SynPat using this form. Synpat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees which will be 50% higher of the amount each Participant paid.</p>\r\n<p>In the event that your License was already acquired by a participant, Synpat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the License to you.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Validated License under this patent portfoio. We call it a Validated License because so many other licensees have validated this patent portfolio since it was introduced by SynPat. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent License Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and upload it using the button below. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 100% higher than the amount each Regular Licensee paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', 0, '<p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">The Syndicate organized by SynPat to fund the Sellerâ€™s Upfront Price will close as soon as SynPat receives requests to participate suffice to fund the Sellerâ€™s Upfront Price.&nbsp;</p><p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><br></p><p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">Defensive and Strategic Licenses are offered, subject to availability, at the following prices:</p><p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><br></p><p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Cost Licensing:</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">During the Syndication period, Defensive and Strategic Licenses are offered at â€œCost Priceâ€ = Upfront Price divided by the total number of Defensive and Strategic Licenses bought by participating companies. &nbsp;Each Participant will pay directly to Seller an amount equal to the Cost Price multiplied by the number of Licenses it acquires. To avoid â€œpredationâ€, a Participant may acquire up to one Strategic License.&nbsp;</p><p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><br></p><p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Regular Licensing:</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">During the four (4) month period following the closing of the syndicate, Defensive and Strategic Licenses are offered at 50% markup on top of the Cost Price, i.e, at a price equal to 1.5 x Cost Price (â€œRegular Priceâ€).</p><p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><br></p><p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Risk Averse Licensing:</span></p><p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">After the four (4) month Regular Licensing stage, Defensive and Strategic Licenses are offered at a premium price, equal to twice the Regular Price (â€œValidated Priceâ€), reflecting the marketâ€™s acknowledgment and validation of the Licenses and the underlying patents.</p><p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><br></p><p dir="ltr" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">Companies participating in the Syndicate will receive from SynPat an amount equal to â…“ of all revenues from the Regular and Late Licensing, divided among the Participants pro-rata to the number licenses bought by each.</p>', '12345', '', 'admin@123', '', '12345', NULL, '', '12345', NULL, '12345', '12345', '', '12345', '', '12345', '', 'admin@123'),
(125, '', 'Hernandez_(4G_LTE_Infrastructure)', 52380, '', 'Hernandez (4G LTE Infrastructure)', '<p>1. Locate and select your company''s name from the list of invitees.</p>\r\n<p>2. Set the stages at which other companies might join the Progam,&nbsp;either as a Participant, a Regular Licensee, or a Late Licensee.</p>\r\n<p>3. Create different scenarios and see how each affects the cost of your license.</p>\r\n<p>4. Decide whether you would like to joint the Program and at which stage.&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '12345', '12345', 0, '12345', '', '0.0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<blockquote>\r\n<h4>Introduction:</h4>\r\n<p>This patent portofolio comprises of 21 US granted patents across 5 families related to Interactive Media and Questionnaire systems, and 13 pending patent applications. There are no foreign counterparts in these patent families.</p>\r\n<p>The technology portfolio comprises of fundamental patents in the following technology areas: Interactive Media Creation &amp; Distribution specifically content delivery for portable wireless devices such as mobile phones, tablet pc&rsquo;s (Dynamic/Interactive contents such as Mobile Questionnaire Systems, Guided Activities &amp; Advertisements, Local Sharing of Content by mobile devices, and Color detection in mobile devices)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The earliest priority date in the poraolio is November 22, 2006.</li>\r\n<li>Encumbrances: None. No buyer restrictions.</li>\r\n<li class="ms-hover">Sell-side Adviser: ICEBERGPrice expectation: US $3m.</li>\r\n<li class="ms-hover">Evidence of Use analysis suggesting infringement by Google, Apple, SurveyMonkey and SurveyMini.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Legal Discussion:</h4>\r\n</blockquote>', '<blockquote>\r\n<p>You may use this Program Simulator to figure out whether to acquire a license under this patent portfolio, and if so, at which stage of the Program. If you decide to particpate in the Syndicae, the Simulator may assit you in figuring out what amout to state in your Request to Participate.</p>\r\n<p>The table on the left had side consists of the list of companies that were invited to participate in the Syndicate. Using the Stage button next to each company''s name, you can create different scenarios: which companies with participate in the Syndicate to fund the acqusition, which companies will buy licenses as Regular Licensees, and which companies will wait and acquire licenses as Risk Averse Licenses.</p>\r\n<p>Keep in mind these basic principles:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class="ms-hover">Participants'' license fee is the "cost price", which is simply the Seller''s asking price divided by the number of participants. Since participants are entitled to one third of any license fees received from licensees who don''t participate in the syndicate, the "net cost" for participants is the cost price minus the each participant''s share in the future revenues.</li>\r\n<li>Regular licensees - companies that decide to acquire a license during the first 4 months after the close of the syndicate and the acquisition of the patents pay regular price, which is 50% above the cost price.</li>\r\n<li>Validated Prices are the price a company will pay if acquires the license at any time after the first 4 months. The validated price is twice the regular price.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</blockquote>', '<p>The following patent purchase agreement is the one executed between the patent seller and SynPat.</p>', '<p>The following document is an offer to contract under a patent license agreement, conditioned upon a successful syndication. SynPat is bound by the terms of the executed offer, and licensees may simply download the offer and accept it.</p>', '<p>In order to participate in this syndicate, you must download the Request to Participate form below fill it in with: 1. the maximum amount that you are willing to contribute into the syndicate. 2. whether you would like to acquire SynPat''s rights to license a third party, and the name of the designated party. Receiving the maximum amount that you would be willing to pay to participate would allow SynPat to determine whether the Seller''s asking price could be raised and the syndicate could be close. It is essential that you send your indication of interest to participate as soon as possible, mainly because the syndicate could close before you do that, but also because another participant might ask to acquire your license. If that happens before you send your request to participate, SynPat Program - Process and Procedure mandates that your license to be sold to that requesting participants.</p>', '<p>The following information was diligently collected in effort to enable prospect participants and licensees to make an informed decision whether or not to join this syndicate or to buy a license with high level of confidence and comfort. Please challenge the data provided here, and send us any inaccuracies, if found, so that we can amend it and share it with others.</p>', '', '<p>The following content is imported from ClaimCharts.info, a free platform that facilitates crowdsourcing of patent infringement and prior art research. Every uploaded claim is broken into its elements and sent to a network of independent subject matter experts who conduct their researches to find evidence that each of the claim elements is either implemented (ClaimChart Report) or anticipated (PriorArt Report). Interested parties may acquire the reports directly from the experts at prices set by the experts.</p>', '<p>The following content is imported from ClaimCharts.info, a free platform that facilitates crowdsourcing of patent infringement and prior art research. Every uploaded claim is broken into its elements and sent to a network of independent subject matter experts who conduct their researches to find evidence that each of the claim elements is either implemented (ClaimChart Report) or anticipated (PriorArt Report). Interested parties may acquire the reports directly from the experts at prices set by the experts.</p>', '<p>This is the text for program</p>', '<blockquote>\r\n<h4>Syndication Process:</h4>\r\n<p>The Syndication Process is explained and illustrated in the figre below, with the below paragraph numbers corresponding to the enumerated steps in the illustration.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>The process is initiated upon SynPat&rsquo;s execution of a Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) with a patent seller at the Seller&rsquo;s Upfront Price (SUP). The PPA includes a closing deadline of 100 days.</li>\r\n<li>SynPat extends to operating companies executed offers to license the patents at prices equal to the SUP divided by the Number of Participants (NoP) in the syndicate. SynPat provides the PPA along with diligence materials to facilitate review of the patents.</li>\r\n<li class="ms-hover">Companies that wish to participate in the syndicate must send SynPat a Request to Participate, stating the maximum license fee they commit to pay.</li>\r\n<li>To proceed with the syndication, SynPat accepts commitments from operating companies, the sum of which must be sufficient to fund the Purchase Price. If not, then in efforts to cover the shortfall, SynPat may try to raise funds from investors (not shown).</li>\r\n<li>Upon receipt of Requests to Participate with aggregate commitments sufficient to pay the SUP, SynPat notifies Seller of the syndicate formation, which effectuates the licenses to all the participants.</li>\r\n<li>SynPat sends to all requesters a Payment Notice stating the exact License Fee (= the SUP divided by NoP)</li>\r\n<li>Participants then counter execute the License Agreement, and pay their License Fee within seven calendar days directly to the Seller&rsquo;s bank account.</li>\r\n<li>Upon full payment of the SUP to the Seller, the Patents are assigned to SynPat.</li>\r\n</ol></blockquote>', '<p>This is damage text1.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<p>If you would like to suggest revisions to the language of the License Agreement, the Request to Participate, or even the Program - Process and Policies, you may download these documents in a MS-Word (.docx) format make your tracked edits and then submit them to SynPat''s review by uploading your files using the buttons below. SynPat will consider the changes requested by all potential participants during the first three weeks form the introduction day of this portfolio, and release updated versions of all three documents.</p>', '', '', '', '', 1, 'The Syndication stage of this portfolio has completed. At this time, you may acquire a Regular License', 'The Syndication stage of this portfolio has completed.  At this time, you may acquire a Regular License', 'Risk Averse Licenses will be available upon completion of both the Syndication and the Regular Licensing stages.', '<p>Thank you for your interest in participating in this syndicate. Please feel free to contact me with any questions. As you may know, the participation fee is calculated by dividing the Seller''s Upfront Price by the number of Participants. Please download the Request to Participate from the Documents tab, fill it out and submit it to SynPat, using this form.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Regular License under this portfoio. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent Licensee Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and submit it to SynPat using this form. Synpat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees which will be 50% higher of the amount each Participant paid.</p>\r\n<p>In the event that your License was already acquired by a participant, Synpat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the License to you.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Validated License under this patent portfoio. We call it a Validated License because so many other licensees have validated this patent portfolio since it was introduced by SynPat. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent License Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and upload it using the button below. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 100% higher than the amount each Regular Licensee paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', 0, NULL, '12345', '', 'admin@123', '', '12345', NULL, '', '12345', NULL, '12345', '12345', '', '12345', '', '12345', '', 'admin@123');
