rmine whether the Seller''s asking price could be raised and the syndicate could be close. It is essential that you send your indication of interest to participate as soon as possible, mainly because the syndicate could close before you do that, but also because another participant might ask to acquire your license. If that happens before you send your request to participate, SynPat Program - Process and Procedure mandates that your license to be sold to that requesting participants.</p>', '<p>The following information was diligently collected in effort to enable prospect participants and licensees to make an informed decision whether or not to join this syndicate or to buy a license with high level of confidence and comfort. Please challenge the data provided here, and send us any inaccuracies, if found, so that we can amend it and share it with others.</p>', '', '<p>The following content is imported from ClaimCharts.info, a free platform that facilitates crowdsourcing of patent infringement and prior art research. Every uploaded claim is broken into its elements and sent to a network of independent subject matter experts who conduct their researches to find evidence that each of the claim elements is either implemented (ClaimChart Report) or anticipated (PriorArt Report). Interested parties may acquire the reports directly from the experts at prices set by the experts.</p>', '<p>The following content is imported from ClaimCharts.info, a free platform that facilitates crowdsourcing of patent infringement and prior art research. Every uploaded claim is broken into its elements and sent to a network of independent subject matter experts who conduct their researches to find evidence that each of the claim elements is either implemented (ClaimChart Report) or anticipated (PriorArt Report). Interested parties may acquire the reports directly from the experts at prices set by the experts.</p>', '<p>This is the text for program</p>', '<blockquote>\n<h4>Syndication Process:</h4>\n<p>The Syndication Process is explained and illustrated in the figre below, with the below paragraph numbers corresponding to the enumerated steps in the illustration.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The process is initiated upon SynPatâ€™s execution of a Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) with a patent seller at the Sellerâ€™s Upfront Price (SUP). The PPA includes a closing deadline of 100 days.</li>\n<li class="ms-hover">SynPat extends to operating companies executed offers to license the patents at prices equal to the SUP divided by the Number of Participants (NoP) in the syndicate. SynPat provides the PPA along with diligence materials to facilitate review of the patents.</li>\n<li class="ms-hover">Companies that wish to participate in the syndicate must send SynPat a Request to Participate, stating the maximum license fee they commit to pay.</li>\n<li>To proceed with the syndication, SynPat accepts commitments from operating companies, the sum of which must be sufficient to fund the Purchase Price. If not, then in efforts to cover the shortfall, SynPat may try to raise funds from investors (not shown).</li>\n<li>Upon receipt of Requests to Participate with aggregate commitments sufficient to pay the SUP, SynPat notifies Seller of the syndicate formation, which effectuates the licenses to all the participants.</li>\n<li>SynPat sends to all requesters a Payment Notice stating the exact License Fee (= the SUP divided by NoP)</li>\n<li>Participants then counter execute the License Agreement, and pay their License Fee within seven calendar days directly to the Sellerâ€™s bank account.</li>\n<li>Upon full payment of the SUP to the Seller, the Patents are assigned to SynPat.</li>\n</ol></blockquote>', '<p>This is damage text1.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/dev2/public/upload/', '', '', '', '', '<p>If you would like to suggest revisions to the language of the License Agreement, the Request to Participate, or even the Program - Process and Policies, you may 