rt. Please challenge the data provided here, and send us any inaccuracies, if found, so that we can amend it and share it with others.</p>', '', '<p>The following content is imported from ClaimCharts.info, a free platform that facilitates crowdsourcing of patent infringement and prior art research. Every uploaded claim is broken into its elements and sent to a network of independent subject matter experts who conduct their researches to find evidence that each of the claim elements is either implemented (ClaimChart Report) or anticipated (PriorArt Report). Interested parties may acquire the reports directly from the experts at prices set by the experts.</p>', '<p>The following content is imported from ClaimCharts.info, a free platform that facilitates crowdsourcing of patent infringement and prior art research. Every uploaded claim is broken into its elements and sent to a network of independent subject matter experts who conduct their researches to find evidence that each of the claim elements is either implemented (ClaimChart Report) or anticipated (PriorArt Report). Interested parties may acquire the reports directly from the experts at prices set by the experts.</p>', '<p>This is the text for program</p>', '<blockquote>\n<h4>Syndication Process:</h4>\n<p>The Syndication Process is explained and illustrated in the figre below, with the below paragraph numbers corresponding to the enumerated steps in the illustration.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The process is initiated upon SynPatâ€™s execution of a Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) with a patent seller at the Sellerâ€™s Upfront Price (SUP). The PPA includes a closing deadline of 100 days.</li>\n<li class="ms-hover">SynPat extends to operating companies executed offers to license the patents at prices equal to the SUP divided by the Number of Participants (NoP) in the syndicate. SynPat provides the PPA along with diligence materials to facilitate review of the patents.</li>\n<li class="ms-hover">Companies that wish to participa