(135, '', 'Pre-Lead', 51244837, '', 'Pre-Lead', '<p>1. Locate and select your company''s name from the list of invitees.</p>\r\n<p>2. Set the stages at which other companies might join the Progam,&nbsp;either as a Participant, a Regular Licensee, or a Late Licensee.</p>\r\n<p>3. Create different scenarios and see how each affects the cost of your license.</p>\r\n<p>4. Decide whether you would like to joint the Program and at which stage.&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '12345', '12345', 0, '12345', '', '0.0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<blockquote>\n<h4>Introduction:</h4>\n<p>This patent portofolio comprises of 21 US granted patents across 5 families related to Interactive Media and Questionnaire systems, and 13 pending patent applications. There are no foreign counterparts in these patent families.</p>\n<p>The technology portfolio comprises of fundamental patents in the following technology areas: Interactive Media Creation &amp; Distribution specifically content delivery for portable wireless devices such as mobile phones, tablet pcâ€™s (Dynamic/Interactive contents such as Mobile Questionnaire Systems, Guided Activities &amp; Advertisements, Local Sharing of Content by mobile devices, and Color detection in mobile devices)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The earliest priority date in the poraolio is November 22, 2006.</li>\n<li>Encumbrances: None. No buyer restrictions.</li>\n<li class="ms-hover">Sell-side Adviser: ICEBERGPrice expectation: US $3m.</li>\n<li class="ms-hover">Evidence of Use analysis suggesting infringement by Google, Apple, SurveyMonkey and SurveyMini.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Legal Discussion:</h4>\n</blockquote>', '<blockquote>\n<p>You may use this Program Simulator to figure out whether to acquire a license under this patent portfolio, and if so, at which stage of the Program. If you decide to particpate in the Syndicae, the Simulator may assit you in figuring out what amout to state in your Request to Participate.</p>\n<p>The table on the left had side consists of the list of companies that were invited to participate in the Syndicate. Using the Stage button next to each company''s name, you can create different scenarios: which companies with participate in the Syndicate to fund the acqusition, which companies will buy licenses as Regular Licensees, and which companies will wait and acquire licenses as Risk Averse Licenses.</p>\n<p>Keep in mind these basic principles:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class="ms-hover">Participants'' license fee is the "cost price", which is simply the Seller''s asking price divided by the number of participants. Since participants are entitled to one third of any license fees received from licensees who don''t participate in the syndicate, the "net cost" for participants is the cost price minus the each participant''s share in the future revenues.</li>\n<li>Regular licensees - companies that decide to acquire a license during the first 4 months after the close of the syndicate and the acquisition of the patents pay regular price, which is 50% above the cost price.</li>\n<li>Validated Prices are the price a company will pay if acquires the license at any time after the first 4 months. The validated price is twice the regular price.</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>', 'This page contains a copy of the actual Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) as executed between the seller of this patent portfolio and SynPat as a buyer. You are welcome to review the details and terms of the transaction. This agreement is subject to confidentiality terms, and the parties agreed to expose the agreement to you as a potential Participant or a Licensee, but not to others. Please respect the parties'' agreement and kindly refrain from disclosing it to third parties.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>You may also find here a draft of the Patent License Agreement (PLA) ready to be executed between SynPat as a licensor and you, either as a Participant or as a licensee. The same PLA is used whether you are a Participant, a Regular Licensee, or Late (Risk Averse) Licensee.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>The third document is a draft of the Strategic License Agreement (SLA) in case you would like to acquire from SynPat the rights to license (and enforce this patent portfolio on) a designated third party, perhaps one of your competitors. While the price of a regular non-exclusive license under the PLA changes from Cost Price to Regular Price and then to Validated Price, the price of Strategic License is always a Regular Price regardless of the time it is purchased.</div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><br></span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">The PPP is a long document that describes the entire program including the different mechanisms that determine the pricing, timing, and procedure.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><br></span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">The last document - and the most important - is your Request to Participate (RTP). When you decide that you wish to participate in the syndication to fund the acquisition of this patent portfolio - whether because you want a non-exclusive license, a strategic license, or simply for the great ROI expected for Participants, go ahead and download this two-page form, fill in the maximum amount you would like to contribute to the syndicate and send it to us using the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page. Please note that your participation fee will be determined according to the formula: Seller''s Asking Price / Number of Participants. &nbsp;The maximum amount that you state on your RTP is only an indication of your intention used for SynPat to figure out whether or not it has requests from potential participants that cumulatively suffice to close the syndicate. At the end, all Participants will pay the same - according to the above simple formula.</span><div><br></div><div>All the documents can be downloaded and revised by our customers. It''s like