(136, '', 'Auriga_Measurement_Systems_', 48192967, '', 'Auriga Measurement Systems ', '<p>1. Locate and select your company''s name from the list of invitees.</p>\r\n<p>2. Set the stages at which other companies might join the Progam,&nbsp;either as a Participant, a Regular Licensee, or a Late Licensee.</p>\r\n<p>3. Create different scenarios and see how each affects the cost of your license.</p>\r\n<p>4. Decide whether you would like to joint the Program and at which stage.&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '12345', '12345', 0, '12345', '', '0.0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<blockquote>\n<h4>Introduction:</h4>\n<p>This patent portofolio comprises of 21 US granted patents across 5 families related to Interactive Media and Questionnaire systems, and 13 pending patent applications. There are no foreign counterparts in these patent families.</p>\n<p>The technology portfolio comprises of fundamental patents in the following technology areas: Interactive Media Creation &amp; Distribution specifically content delivery for portable wireless devices such as mobile phones, tablet pcâ€™s (Dynamic/Interactive contents such as Mobile Questionnaire Systems, Guided Activities &amp; Advertisements, Local Sharing of Content by mobile devices, and Color detection in mobile devices)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The earliest priority date in the poraolio is November 22, 2006.</li>\n<li>Encumbrances: None. No buyer restrictions.</li>\n<li class="ms-hover">Sell-side Adviser: ICEBERGPrice expectation: US $3m.</li>\n<li class="ms-hover">Evidence of Use analysis suggesting infringement by Google, Apple, SurveyMonkey and SurveyMini.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Legal Discussion:</h4>\n</blockquote>', '<blockquote>\n<p>You may use this Program Simulator to figure out whether to acquire a license under this patent portfolio, and if so, at which stage of the Program. If you decide to particpate in the Syndicae, the Simulator may assit you in figuring out what amout to state in your Request to Participate.</p>\n<p>The table on the left had side consists of the list of companies that were invited to participate in the Syndicate. Using the Stage button next to each company''s name, you can create different scenarios: which companies with participate in the Syndicate to fund the acqusition, which companies will buy licenses as Regular Licensees, and which companies will wait and acquire licenses as Risk Averse Licenses.</p>\n<p>Keep in mind these basic principles:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class="ms-hover">Participants'' license fee is the "cost price", which is simply the Seller''s asking price divided by the number of participants. Since participants are entitled to one third of any license fees received from licensees who don''t participate in the syndicate, the "net cost" for participants is the cost price minus the each participant''s share in the future revenues.</li>\n<li>Regular licensees - companies that decide to acquire a license during the first 4 months after the close of the syndicate and the acquisition of the patents pay regular price, which is 50% above the cost price.</li>\n<li>Validated Prices are the price a company will pay if acquires the license at any time after the first 4 months. The validated price is twice the regular price.</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>', 'This page contains a copy of the actual Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) as executed between the seller of this patent portfolio and SynPat as a buyer. You are welcome to review the details and terms of the transaction. This agreement is subject to confidentiality terms, and the parties agreed to expose the agreement to you as a potential Participant or a Licensee, but not to others. Please respect the parties'' agreement and kindly refrain from disclosing it to third parties.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>You may also find here a draft of the Patent License Agreement (PLA) ready to be executed between SynPat as a licensor and you, either as a Participant or as a licensee. The same PLA is used whether you are a Participant, a Regular Licensee, or Late (Risk Averse) Licensee.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>The third document is a draft of the Strategic License Agreement (SLA) in case you would like to acquire from SynPat the rights to license (and enforce this patent portfolio on) a designated third party, perhaps one of your competitors. While the price of a regular non-exclusive license under the PLA changes from Cost Price to Regular Price and then to Validated Price, the price of Strategic License is always a Regular Price regardless of the time it is purchased.</div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><br></span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">The PPP is a long document that describes the entire program including the different mechanisms that determine the pricing, timing, and procedure.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><br></span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">The last document - and the most important - is your Request to Participate (RTP). When you decide that you wish to participate in the syndication to fund the acquisition of this patent portfolio - whether because you want a non-exclusive license, a strategic license, or simply for the great ROI expected for Participants, go ahead and download this two-page form, fill in the maximum amount you would like to contribute to the syndicate and send it to us using the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page. Please note that your participation fee will be determined according to the formula: Seller''s Asking Price / Number of Participants. &nbsp;The maximum amount that you state on your RTP is only an indication of your intention used for SynPat to figure out whether or not it has requests from potential participants that cumulatively suffice to close the syndicate. At the end, all Participants will pay the same - according to the above simple formula.</span><div><br></div><div>All the documents can be downloaded and revised by our customers. It''s like when you enter a department store to buy a suit and you find the one you like at the right shape and size, still there are always a few minor modifications to be made so the suit will fits you perfectly. The same here: although SynPat''s licenses are standard, still we always allow our customers to make those few minor modifications as to make their licenses fit them perfectly. Feel free to review and download the documents below and if you like to add your minor modifications please do so and upload your files back to SynPat. We will review your revisions and get back to you swiftly.</div></div>', '<p>The following document is an offer to contract under a patent license agreement, conditioned upon a successful syndication. SynPat is bound by the terms of the executed offer, and licensees may simply download the offer and accept it.</p>', '<p>In order to participate in this syndicate, you must download the Request to Participate form below fill it in with: 1. the maximum amount that you are willing to contribute into the syndicate. 2. whether you would like to acquire SynPat''s rights to license a third party, and the name of the designated party. Receiving the maximum amount that you would be willing to pay to participate would allow SynPat to determine whether the Seller''s asking price could be raised and the syndicate could be close. It is essential that you send your indication of interest to participate as soon as possible, mainly because the syndicate could close before you do that, but also because another participant might ask to acquire your license. If that happens before you send your request to participate, SynPat Program - Process and Procedure mandates that your license to be sold to that requesting participants.</p>', '<p>The following information was diligently collected in effort to enable prospect participants and licensees to make an informed decision whether or not to join this syndicate or to buy a license with high level of confidence and comfort. Please challenge the data provided here, and send us any inaccuracies, if found, so that we can amend it and share it with others.</p>', '', '<p>The following content is imported from ClaimCharts.info, a free platform that facilitates crowdsourcing of patent infringement and prior art research. Every uploaded claim is broken into its elements and sent to a network of independent subject matter experts who conduct their researches to find evidence that each of the claim elements is either implemented (ClaimChart Report) or anticipated (PriorArt Report). Interested parties may acquire the reports directly from the experts at prices set by the experts.</p>', '<p>The following content is imported from ClaimCharts.info, a free platform that facilitates crowdsourcing of patent infringement and prior art research. Every uploaded claim is broken into its elements and sent to a network of independent subject matter experts who conduct their researches to find evidence that each of the claim elements is either implemented (ClaimChart Report) or anticipated (PriorArt Report). Interested parties may acquire the reports directly from the experts at prices set by the experts.</p>', '<p>This is the text for program</p>', '<blockquote>\n<h4>Syndication Process:</h4>\n<p>The Syndication Process is explained and illustrated in the figre below, with the below paragraph numbers corresponding to the enumerated steps in the illustration.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The process is initiated upon SynPatâ€™s execution of a Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) with a patent seller at the Sellerâ€™s Upfront Price (SUP). The PPA includes a closing deadline of 100 days.</li>\n<li class="ms-hover">SynPat extends to operating companies executed offers to license the patents at prices equal to the SUP divided by the Number of Participants (NoP) in the syndicate. SynPat provides the PPA along with diligence materials to facilitate review of the patents.</li>\n<li class="ms-hover">Companies that wish to participate in the syndicate must send SynPat a Request to Participate, stating the maximum license fee they commit to pay.</li>\n<li>To proceed with the syndication, SynPat accepts commitments from operating companies, the sum of which must be sufficient to fund the Purchase Price. If not, then in efforts to cover the shortfall, SynPat may try to raise funds from investors (not shown).</li>\n<li>Upon receipt of Requests to Participate with aggregate commitments sufficient to pay the SUP, SynPat notifies Seller of the syndicate formation, which effectuates the licenses to all the participants.</li>\n<li>SynPat sends to all requesters a Payment Notice stating the exact License Fee (= the SUP divided by NoP)</li>\n<li>Participants then counter execute the License Agreement, and pay their License Fee within seven calendar days directly to the Sellerâ€™s bank account.</li>\n<li>Upon full payment of the SUP to the Seller, the Patents are assigned to SynPat.</li>\n</ol></blockquote>', '<p>This is damage text1.</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<p>If you would like to suggest revisions to the language of the License Agreement, the Request to Participate, or even the Program - Process and Policies, you may download these documents in a MS-Word (.docx) format make your tracked edits and then submit them to SynPat''s review by uploading your files using the buttons below. SynPat will consider the changes requested by all potential participants during the first three weeks form the introduction day of this portfolio, and release updated versions of all three documents.</p>', '', '', '', '', 1, 'The Syndication stage of this portfolio has completed. At this time, you may acquire a Regular License', 'The Syndication stage of this portfolio has completed.  At this time, you may acquire a Regular License', 'Risk Averse Licenses will be available upon completion of both the Syndication and the Regular Licensing stages.', '<p>Thank you for