style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Claim Charts:</span>&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 20.8px;">SynPat posted an order on ClaimCharts.info - a third party application - to produce claim charts reports. Via this online platform, subject matter experts were invited to study and prepare reports showing evidence of use, addressing each and every element of select claims from this portfolio. Posting of reports under the Claim Charts section is done automatically. Click on the patent(claim) number to see whether claim charts reports were submitted. If there are any, you may click the BUY button and purchase the reports using Paypal payment directly to the author of the report - the subject matter expert person or firm who prepared it. The prices and content of such reports are not the responsibility of SynPat.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Comparables:</span> Although SynPat offers licenses at three fixed prices: Cost Price = SUP/NoP, Regular Price = 1.5 x Cost Price, and Validated Price = 2 x Regular Price, in order to assist our customers in making informed decisions and properly evaluate this opportunity, it is useful to take into consideration alternative pricing. This section contains documents that can teach about the reasonable royalty rates that are relevant to this patent portfolio, as well as a sample of patent license agreements covering technologies with characteristics that are similar to the subject patents.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Royalty Rate Study:</span> S</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">ince patent licensing markets are known to be highly inefficient, and market transaction data is subject to significant error, the license fee appraisal process generally relies on multiple simultaneous approaches to value, with a judgemental reconciliation as the final step to arrive at the appraiser''s opinion. Thus, an Expert Royalty Rate Study was conducted specifically for this portfolio in an effort to identify the applicable range of reasonable royalty rates.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">License Fee Estimator:</span> After reviewing the comprables and studying the Expert Royalty Rate Study, you''ll be able to effectively use the License Fee Estimator to quickly and simply estimate your specific alternative cost of a license under this portfolio following these steps:</span></p><p></p><ol><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Apply your judgement to figure out the Maximum Royalty Rate and the Minimum Royalty Rate that could be applied to this portfolio, and plug them in the Estimator to calculate the </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: underline;">average</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> royalty rate.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Use the handle bar to adjust the average royalty rate in order to take into consideration and reflect specific circumstances that require a higher or lower rate, in order to obtain the </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: underline;">reasonable</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> royalty rate.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Enter your average addressable sales that might be found covered by the parent portfolio.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Enter the relevant number of years of an applicable license.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Calculate your expected alternative license fee.</span><br></li></ol><p></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p>', '<p>The following content is aimed to demonstrate the quality of this portfolio. We use the term quality to relate to the likelihood of a licensing campaign to sustain challenges. The materials below contains information on the existence of licenses granted under this portfolio, and if there are any - to the nature of such licenses. Most of the information in this page is not publicly available, and therefore was provided by the seller. This page also contains information about the chain of title, and addresses irregularities or missing items that might make the potentially transferred title questionable or unclear. In some cases, when needed, we provided the agreements showing assignments along the life of the patents. We also included declarations and information by the seller with regard to the involvement and rights of third parties such as universities and governmental agencies that might pose challenges and hardship in future licensing. Involvement of the inventors or the seller in industry standard activities and the existence of potential commitments to different SSO to FRAND terms licensing is also addressed. Next are data relating to collateral by creditors and other third parties that might encumber the portfolio and the ability to license it. We also included reports from patent offices relating to payment of maintenance fees, and other activities that might affect a the licensing power. Information on backward citations is provided as well, and is aimed to show whether and to what extent the inventor and examiner addressed prior arts.</p><p>SynPat posted an order on ClaimCharts.info - a third party application - to produce prior art reports. Via this online platform, subject matter experts were invited to study and prepare reports showing invalidating prior art, addressing each and every element of select claims from this portfolio. Posting of reports under the Prior Art section is done automatically. Click on the patent(claim) number to see whether prior art reports were submitted. If there are any, you may click the BUY button and purchase the reports using Paypal payment directly to the author of the report - the subject matter expert person or firm who prepared it. The prices and content of such reports are not the responsibility of SynPat.</p>', '', '', '<div><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">The Syndication Process:</span></div><div><br></div><div>The Syndication Process is explained and illustrated below:</div><div><ol><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">We begin with the execution of a Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) between a patent seller and SynPat, which defines the list of patents to be acquired by SynPat, Sellerâ€™s Upfront Price (SUP), and the deadline for closing the syndicate, which is generally 100 days from the PPA''s effective date.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">SynPat begins an extensive due diligence during which it invite operating companies to participate in crowdfunding the SUP. The invitations to participate include a copy of the PPA, a draft Patent License Agreement (PLA) under which SynPat will grant the license under the acquired patent portfolio to interested customers, a draft Strategic License under interested customers will be able to acquire the exclusive rights to license the acquired patents to a designated company of its choice (provided such a company has not yet purchased a license), a Request to Participate form, which which interested customers can submit to SynPat their commitments to participate in the syndicate, and finally, a copy of the program terms - a document that explains the SynPat licensing stages.&nbsp;</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Companies that wish to participate in the syndicate must send to SynPat a Request to Participate, stating the maximum license fee they commit to pay. Clicking the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page would allow you to submit your executed Request to Participate together with any comments, requests, or instructions to SynPat. Upon doing that, you''ll receive an immediate confirmation on receiving your request. Please keep in mind that your participation is secured and you will be considered a participant when SynPat receives commitments from interested companies, sufficient to equally crowdfund the SUP, and your committed amount is equal or greater than the SUP divided by the number of participating companies (NoP).</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Upon receiving Requests to Participate from interested companies, sufficient to equally crowdfund the SUP, SynPat will notify the Seller of the successful syndicate formation. The notice to Seller effectuates the licenses to all the participants. Note that licenses to participants become effective before the fee is paid by them.&nbsp;</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Next, SynPat sends to all participants a Payment Notice stating the exact participation fee to be paid (= SUP/NoP).</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Participants then counter execute the License Agreement, and pay their participation fee within seven calendar days. Please note that payments are to be made directly to the Sellerâ€™s bank account, as stated in the PPA and the PLA.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Upon full payment of the SUP to the Seller, the title to the acquired patents is assigned to SynPat. Note that a failure to pay a participation fee by any participant does not affect the validity of your licenses. Rest assured that your license is in full effect upon your receiving a Payment Notice from SynPat.</span><br></li></ol></div>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<div>This page contains the following documents and functionalities:</div><div><br></div><div><span style="transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">PURCHASE AGREEMENT</span>&nbsp;- a copy of the actual Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) as executed between the seller of this patent portfolio and SynPat as a buyer. This agreement is subject to confidentiality terms, and the parties agreed to expose the agreement to you as a potential Participant or a Licensee, but not to others. Please respect the parties'' agreement and kindly refrain from disclosing it to third parties.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">NON-EXCLUSIVE LICENSE</span>&nbsp;- a draft of SynPat standard Patent License Agreement. This agreement is applicable to all licensees whether they acquire their licenses as Participants, Regular Licensees, or Late Licensees. The difference is in the prices paid in exchange for the non-exclusive license. Participants pay the Cost Price = SUP/NoP and are entitled <span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">to receive from SynPat an equal share of 1/3 of all license fees received from licensees who did participate in the syndicate. Regular Licensees'' pay the Regular Price = 1.5 x Cost Price, and Late Licensees pay the Validated Price - 2 x Regular Price.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">STRATEGIC LICENSE</span>&nbsp;- a draft of SynPat standard Strategic License Agreement (SLA) in case you would like to acquire from SynPat the rights to license (and enforce this patent portfolio on) a designated third party, perhaps one of your competitors. While the price of a regular non-exclusive license under the PLA changes from Cost Price to Regular Price and then to Validated Price, the price of Strategic License is always a Regular Price regardless of the time it is purchased.</div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">REQUEST TO PARTICIPATE</span><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">&nbsp;- the Request to Participate (RTP) form is used to by companies to inform SynPat about their intention to participate in the syndicate to crowdfund the SUP. To use this form, download and print it, fill it in and execute it, then use the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page to upload and submit it to SynPat. Please note that your participation fee will be determined according to the formula: Seller''s Asking Price / Number of Participants. &nbsp;The maximum amount that you state on your RTP is for SynPat to figure out whether your request is suffice for participation taking into consideration the requsts submitted by others. Ultimately, you, like all all other Participants will pay the same amount: Cost Price = SUP/NoP.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">PROGRAM</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">&nbsp;- The SynPat Program Procedure and Policies (PPP) describes in details the unique licensing approach offered by SynPat.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><br></span></div><div><span style="color: inherit; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">DOWNLOAD / UPLOAD</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">&nbsp;- From this page customers can download the above documents. If you would like to suggest revisions to the language of any of the documents you may do so by downloading them, making your tracked edits and submitting them back to SynPat using the form on this page.</span></div>', '', '', '', '', 1, 'The Syndication stage of this portfolio has completed. At this time, you may acquire a Regular License', 'The Syndication stage for this portfolio is still open, and you may acquire a license as a Participant. Regular Licenses will be available upon a successful syndication.', 'Risk Averse Licenses will be available upon completion of both the Syndication and the Regular Licensing stages.', '<p>Thank you for your interest in participating in this syndicate. Please feel free to contact me with any questions. As you may know, the participation fee is calculated by dividing the Seller''s Upfront Price by the number of Participants. Please download the Request to Participate from the Documents tab, fill it out and submit it to SynPat, using this form.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Regular License under this portfoio. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent Licensee Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and submit it to SynPat using this form. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 50% higher than the price each Participant paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired (as a Strategic License) by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Validated License under this patent portfoio. We call it a Validated License because so many other licensees have validated this patent portfolio since it was introduced by SynPat. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent License Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and upload it using the button below. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 100% higher than the amount each Regular Licensee paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', 0, NULL, '12345', '', 'admin@123', '', '12345', NULL, '', '12345', NULL, '12345', '12345', '', '12345', '', '12345', '', 'admin@123');
INSERT INTO `licenses` (`id`, `damage`, `license_number`, `serial_number`, `email_address`, `name`, `introduction`, `commitment_file`, `purchase_file`, `syndication_file`, `program_file`, `purchase_license`, `purchase_buy`, `purchase_buy_doc`, `purchase_file_doc`, `purchase_license_doc`, `cliamchart`, `prior_art`, `title`, `access_code`, `due_access_code`, `license_status`, `tabs_access_code`, `expiration_date`, `asking_price`, `portfolio_button_text`, `file_left`, `file_middle`, `file_right`, `file_four`, `file_five`, `file_six`, `file_seven`, `file_eight`, `file_nine`, `file_ten`, `file_eleven`, `file_twelve`, `portfolio_text`, `simulator_text`, `purchase_agreement`, `license_tab`, `buy_a_license_tab`, `due_diligence_tab`, `impact_tab`, `claim_chart_tab`, `prior_art_tab`, `program_tab`, `syndication_tab`, `damage_tab`, `store_tab`, `red_button`, `person_name`, `person_email`, `person_phone`, `person_picture`, `current_requesting_companies`, `program_policies_tab`, `program_policies_file`, `strategic_license_agreement`, `document_text`, `download_ppa`, `download_license`, `download_request`, `download_program_policies`, `active_button`, `deactive_tooltip`, `deactive_tooltip_regular`, `deactive_tooltip_risk`, `popup_text_participant`, `popup_text_regular`, `popup_text_risk`, `visibility`, `price_tab`, `portfolio_access_code`, `portfolio_email_address`, `comparables_admin_code`, `comparables_email_address`, `comparables_access_code`, `guide_for_comparables`, `tech_email_address`, `tech_access_code`, `legal_email_address`, `legal_access_code`, `pdf_access_code`, `pdf_email_address`, `images_access_code`, `images_email_address`, `illus_access_code`, `illus_email_address`, `master_passcode`) VALUES
(153, '', 'Genedics', 22232, 'feingene@yahoo.com', 'Genedics', '<p>1. Locate and select your company''s name from the list of invitees.</p>\r\n<p>2. Set the stages at which other companies might join the Progam,&nbsp;either as a Participant, a Regular Licensee, or a Late Licensee.</p>\r\n<p>3. Create different scenarios and see how each affects the cost of your license.</p>\r\n<p>4. Decide whether you would like to joint the Program and at which stage.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B61I0m5ybHrFeWlrMHBoM3R3N3M/view?usp=drivesdk', '', '', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1zm_cnT35-h0AvmjbxCYr8ejECIk_n-z4VZNq6vWOd-k/edit?usp=drivesdk', '', '', '', '', '<iframe src="http://claimcharts.info/index.php/component/survey/?tmpl=component&task=customer.generateClientRequest&client_id=Genedic&pr=2" width="100%" height="680" frameborder="0" scrolling="yes"></iframe>', '', '', '12345', 'Jacksonhits1', 0, '12345', '05/01/2016', '1.0', '', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFRW93YnA0eE8zLVk', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFZVN0TTE0bndyOWs', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFR3dIa3NCenRzbnc', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFM1gtOTJGSC1zLTQ', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFbzA1cjdyNlRHcVE', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFV3gyemVJNWg2X1E', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFMWZwSWZ6NmJ5ZDA', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFUVZ0UnBuRHNwMlU', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFZ2ZGNXlZZTUtVmM', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFYlBoazZYd29vUGc', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFbVRCaGVLVDl4R0k', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFdm1RLVFHc3ZFSGM', 'SynPat decided to acquire this patent portfolio since it covers many potential licensees who could benefit from obtaining licenses that are unavailable otherwise. This portfolio is directed to a user interface system that enables a user to interact with a 3D holographic image in a 3D coordinate system. Examples of the interaction include twisting, bending, cutting, displacing and squeezing the holographic image.\r\n\r\nCompanies that provide products or are doing research in areas such as 3D Hologram Projectors, 3D Glasses, Heads-Up-Displays (HUDs), Gaming Systems, Medical Holography, Holographic Television and Computer Displays, Smart Phones, Simlators and Virtual Reality Environments may be interested in this patent portfolio.\r\n\r\nThe priority date of this portfolio is Oct 2007. Â The portfolio is comprised of six assets: five US granted patents and one US patent application.\r\n\r\nThe expected number of licensees as they spread along the three segments of the market together with the information provided in this docket support a rational decision to participate in the effort to crowdfund the acquisition of this portfolio.\r\n\r\nSo long as SynPat holds a portfolio of patents, any operating company may submit to SynPat a request to acquire from SynPat either a Defensive License, a Strategic License, or both.\r\n\r\nA Defensive License is a paid up nonexclusive license under the acquired patent portfolio. A Strategic License provides is buyer the right to license any other operating company of its choice (â€œDesignated Third Partyâ€).Â \r\n\r\nA request to acquire a license is always subject to availability. Â For example, a request by Company A to acquire a Strategic License that would allow it to exclusively license Company B must arrive to SynPat before a similar request from Company C, or a request from Company B to acquire a Defensive License is received by SynPat. Also, a request by Company B to acquire a Defensive License must arrive to SynPat before a request from Company A to acquire a Strategic License, which would allow it to exclusively license Company B, is received by SynPat.\r\n\r\nIn guiding its actions, SynPat will use the date and time of actual receipt of any request, and unless the date and time of the request to acquire the right to license a Designated Third Party can be clearly shown to have been received by SynPat prior to a request for a Defensive License by the Designated Third Party, SynPat will honor the request of the Designated Third Party.', '<div>The simulator below is aimed to assist you in figuring out at which of the three stages to acquire your license, once you decided to acquire one. &nbsp;It allows you to simulate scenarios under which several companies purchases licenses by participating in the crowdfunding syndicate, while others acquire their licenses later on as Regular Licensees, and some very conservative ones obtain their licenses as Late Licensees at any time after the Regular Licensing period.</div><div><br></div><div>Price differences:</div><div><ol><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Participants</span> pay a Cost Price, which is simply the Seller''s upfront price divided by the number of participants (SUP/NoP). Since Participants are entitled to receive from SynPat an equal share of 1/3 of all license fees received from licensees who did participate in the syndicate, i.e. from Regular Licensees, and Late Licensees, the "net cost" for each Participant is equal to the Cost Price minus its share in the future sales of licenses.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Regular Licensees</span> - companies that decide to acquire a license during the first 4 months after the close of the syndicate - pay a Regular Price, which is equal to 1.5 x Cost Price.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Late Licensees</span> pay a Validated Price - the price a company will pay if acquires the license at any time after the 4 months Regular Licensing period. The Validated price is equal to 2 x Regular Price.</span><br></li></ol></div><div><br></div><div>The table on the left hand side includes the list of companies that were invited to participate in the Syndicate and to acquire licenses at any later time. Using the Stage button next to each company''s name, you can create different scenarios and determine which companies will participate in the Syndicate, those who will buy licenses as Regular Licensees, and the laggards who will wait and acquire licenses only after many others will have bought the same licenses.</div><div><br></div><div>The three middle tables represent the three stages: Syndicate Participation, Regular Licensing, and Late Licensing, and will include the company names according to your selections and your estimated scenarios.</div><div><br></div><div>The first thing to begin with is to select the radio button next to your company''s name. Doing so will send your company to the first table of Participants. You can move it to different stages by changing the Select Stage button next to your company name.</div><div><br></div><div>Next, use the Select Stage buttons next to the companies you believe will buy a license to determine at which stage each will acquire its license. &nbsp;We believe that the more conservative a company is, the later it will acquire its license. The main reason for that could be the time it takes for such companies to assess the opportunity, decide, and react. Another reason could be the preferences of such companies to allow other companies to validate the quality of the license and the price, taking into consideration that higher price they would pay reflects the confidence they gain.</div>', '', '', '', 'The following information was diligently collected and prepared in effort to enable prospect Participants and Licensees to learn the scope of the inventions included in this portfolio, based on which make informed decisions whether or not to join this syndicate or to buy licenses at later times. We made special efforts to illustrate selected claims, element by element, which you can find under the Illustrations tab. Each mouse click will reveal additional claim element together with a corresponding illustration. This process is aimed to assist in quickly grasping the full scope of the entire claim as a whole. Please feel free to send us any inquiries relating the information provided here.', '<p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">This page is dedicated to demonstrating the impact of this patent portfolio. Impact is associated with the likelihood of a portfolio to generate a large amounts of license fees, which generally happens where the patents cover significant sources of revenues of large number of potential licensees. To learn about the impact of this patent portfolio we provided the following:</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Forward Citations:</span> Since both the applicant and the patent examiner must find and cite documents that may anticipate a claimed invention, the number of forward citations a patent receives, the citing entities, and the pattern of citing may point on the patent''s acknowledgement by others and sometimes even on its significance and relevance to others'' technologies.</span><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ''Open Sans'', arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px;">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Claim Charts:</span>&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 20.8px;">SynPat posted an order on ClaimCharts.info - a third party application - to produce claim charts reports. Via this online platform, subject matter experts were invited to study and prepare reports showing evidence of use, addressing each and every element of select claims from this portfolio. Posting of reports under the Claim Charts section is done automatically. Click on the patent(claim) number to see whether claim charts reports were submitted. If there are any, you may click the BUY button and purchase the reports using Paypal payment directly to the author of the report - the subject matter expert person or firm who prepared it. The prices and content of such reports are not the responsibility of SynPat.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Comparables:</span> Although SynPat offers licenses at three fixed prices: Cost Price = SUP/NoP, Regular Price = 1.5 x Cost Price, and Validated Price = 2 x Regular Price, in order to assist our customers in making informed decisions and properly evaluate this opportunity, it is useful to take into consideration alternative pricing. This section contains documents that can teach about the reasonable royalty rates that are relevant to this patent portfolio, as well as a sample of patent license agreements covering technologies with characteristics that are similar to the subject patents.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Royalty Rate Study:</span> S</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">ince patent licensing markets are known to be highly inefficient, and market transaction data is subject to significant error, the license fee appraisal process generally relies on multiple simultaneous approaches to value, with a judgemental reconciliation as the final step to arrive at the appraiser''s opinion. Thus, an Expert Royalty Rate Study was conducted specifically for this portfolio in an effort to identify the applicable range of reasonable royalty rates.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">License Fee Estimator:</span> After reviewing the comprables and studying the Expert Royalty Rate Study, you''ll be able to effectively use the License Fee Estimator to quickly and simply estimate your specific alternative cost of a license under this portfolio following these steps:</span></p><p></p><ol><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Apply your judgement to figure out the Maximum Royalty Rate and the Minimum Royalty Rate that could be applied to this portfolio, and plug them in the Estimator to calculate the </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: underline;">average</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> royalty rate.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Use the handle bar to adjust the average royalty rate in order to take into consideration and reflect specific circumstances that require a higher or lower rate, in order to obtain the </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: underline;">reasonable</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> royalty rate.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Enter your average addressable sales that might be found covered by the parent portfolio.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Enter the relevant number of years of an applicable license.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Calculate your expected alternative license fee.</span><br></li></ol><p></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p>', '<p>The following content is aimed to demonstrate the quality of this portfolio. We use the term quality to relate to the likelihood of a licensing campaign to sustain challenges. The materials below contains information on the existence of licenses granted under this portfolio, and if there are any - to the nature of such licenses. Most of the information in this page is not publicly available, and therefore was provided by the seller. This page also contains information about the chain of title, and addresses irregularities or missing items that might make the potentially transferred title questionable or unclear. In some cases, when needed, we provided the agreements showing assignments along the life of the patents. We also included declarations and information by the seller with regard to the involvement and rights of third parties such as universities and governmental agencies that might pose challenges and hardship in future licensing. Involvement of the inventors or the seller in industry standard activities and the existence of potential commitments to different SSO to FRAND terms licensing is also addressed. Next are data relating to collateral by creditors and other third parties that might encumber the portfolio and the ability to license it. We also included reports from patent offices relating to payment of maintenance fees, and other activities that might affect a the licensing power. Information on backward citations is provided as well, and is aimed to show whether and to what extent the inventor and examiner addressed prior arts.</p><p>SynPat posted an order on ClaimCharts.info - a third party application - to produce prior art reports. Via this online platform, subject matter experts were invited to study and prepare reports showing invalidating prior art, addressing each and every element of select claims from this portfolio. Posting of reports under the Prior Art section is done automatically. Click on the patent(claim) number to see whether prior art reports were submitted. If there are any, you may click the BUY button and purchase the reports using Paypal payment directly to the author of the report - the subject matter expert person or firm who prepared it. The prices and content of such reports are not the responsibility of SynPat.</p>', '', '', '<div><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">The Syndication Process:</span></div><div><br></div><div>The Syndication Process is explained and illustrated below:</div><div><ol><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">We begin with the execution of a Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) between a patent seller and SynPat, which defines the list of patents to be acquired by SynPat, Sellerâ€™s Upfront Price (SUP), and the deadline for closing the syndicate, which is generally 100 days from the PPA''s effective date.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">SynPat begins an extensive due diligence during which it invite operating companies to participate in crowdfunding the SUP. The invitations to participate include a copy of the PPA, a draft Patent License Agreement (PLA) under which SynPat will grant the license under the acquired patent portfolio to interested customers, a draft Strategic License under interested customers will be able to acquire the exclusive rights to license the acquired patents to a designated company of its choice (provided such a company has not yet purchased a license), a Request to Participate form, which which interested customers can submit to SynPat their commitments to participate in the syndicate, and finally, a copy of the program terms - a document that explains the SynPat licensing stages.&nbsp;</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Companies that wish to participate in the syndicate must send to SynPat a Request to Participate, stating the maximum license fee they commit to pay. Clicking the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page would allow you to submit your executed Request to Participate together with any comments, requests, or instructions to SynPat. Upon doing that, you''ll receive an immediate confirmation on receiving your request. Please keep in mind that your participation is secured and you will be considered a participant when SynPat receives commitments from interested companies, sufficient to equally crowdfund the SUP, and your committed amount is equal or greater than the SUP divided by the number of participating companies (NoP).</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Upon receiving Requests to Participate from interested companies, sufficient to equally crowdfund the SUP, SynPat will notify the Seller of the successful syndicate formation. The notice to Seller effectuates the licenses to all the participants. Note that licenses to participants become effective before the fee is paid by them.&nbsp;</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Next, SynPat sends to all participants a Payment Notice stating the exact participation fee to be paid (= SUP/NoP).</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Participants then counter execute the License Agreement, and pay their participation fee within seven calendar days. Please note that payments are to be made directly to the Sellerâ€™s bank account, as stated in the PPA and the PLA.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Upon full payment of the SUP to the Seller, the title to the acquired patents is assigned to SynPat. Note that a failure to pay a participation fee by any participant does not affect the validity of your licenses. Rest assured that your license is in full effect upon your receiving a Payment Notice from SynPat.</span><br></li></ol></div>', '', '', '', 'Uzi Aloush', 'uzi@synpat.com', '415-805-8813', 'http://backyard.synpat.com/public/upload/', '', '', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1truUHFt-eDnqoSQ-4lBhGK5EtuCgCvYzZBm1rWxDF2o/edit?usp=drivesdk', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1libmeQlQlt4DaamVqMoeE1TONgbfBb20XYueoOeYLB8/edit?usp=drivesdk', '<div>This page contains the following documents and functionalities:</div><div><br></div><div><span style="transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">PURCHASE AGREEMENT</span>&nbsp;- a copy of the actual Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) as executed between the seller of this patent portfolio and SynPat as a buyer. This agreement is subject to confidentiality terms, and the parties agreed to expose the agreement to you as a potential Participant or a Licensee, but not to others. Please respect the parties'' agreement and kindly refrain from disclosing it to third parties.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">NON-EXCLUSIVE LICENSE</span>&nbsp;- a draft of SynPat standard Patent License Agreement. This agreement is applicable to all licensees whether they acquire their licenses as Participants, Regular Licensees, or Late Licensees. The difference is in the prices paid in exchange for the non-exclusive license. Participants pay the Cost Price = SUP/NoP and are entitled <span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">to receive from SynPat an equal share of 1/3 of all license fees received from licensees who did participate in the syndicate. Regular Licensees'' pay the Regular Price = 1.5 x Cost Price, and Late Licensees pay the Validated Price - 2 x Regular Price.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">STRATEGIC LICENSE</span>&nbsp;- a draft of SynPat standard Strategic License Agreement (SLA) in case you would like to acquire from SynPat the rights to license (and enforce this patent portfolio on) a designated third party, perhaps one of your competitors. While the price of a regular non-exclusive license under the PLA changes from Cost Price to Regular Price and then to Validated Price, the price of Strategic License is always a Regular Price regardless of the time it is purchased.</div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">REQUEST TO PARTICIPATE</span><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">&nbsp;- the Request to Participate (RTP) form is used to by companies to inform SynPat about their intention to participate in the syndicate to crowdfund the SUP. To use this form, download and print it, fill it in and execute it, then use the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page to upload and submit it to SynPat. Please note that your participation fee will be determined according to the formula: Seller''s Asking Price / Number of Participants. &nbsp;The maximum amount that you state on your RTP is for SynPat to figure out whether your request is suffice for participation taking into consideration the requsts submitted by others. Ultimately, you, like all all other Participants will pay the same amount: Cost Price = SUP/NoP.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">PROGRAM</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">&nbsp;- The SynPat Program Procedure and Policies (PPP) describes in details the unique licensing approach offered by SynPat.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><br></span></div><div><span style="color: inherit; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">DOWNLOAD / UPLOAD</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">&nbsp;- From this page customers can download the above documents. If you would like to suggest revisions to the language of any of the documents you may do so by downloading them, making your tracked edits and submitting them back to SynPat using the form on this page.</span></div>', '', '', '', '', 1, 'The Syndication stage of this portfolio has completed. At this time, you may acquire a Regular License', 'The Syndication stage for this portfolio is still open, and you may acquire a license as a Participant. Regular Licenses will be available upon a successful syndication.', 'Risk Averse Licenses will be available upon completion of both the Syndication and the Regular Licensing stages.', '<p>Thank you for your interest in participating in this syndicate. Please feel free to contact me with any questions. As you may know, the participation fee is calculated by dividing the Seller''s Upfront Price by the number of Participants. Please download the Request to Participate from the Documents tab, fill it out and submit it to SynPat, using this form.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Regular License under this portfoio. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent Licensee Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and submit it to SynPat using this form. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 50% higher than the price each Participant paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired (as a Strategic License) by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Validated License under this patent portfoio. We call it a Validated License because so many other licensees have validated this patent portfolio since it was introduced by SynPat. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent License Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and upload it using the button below. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 100% higher than the amount each Regular Licensee paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', 0, '<div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap;">The Syndicate organized by SynPat to fund the Seller''s Upfront Price will close as soon as SynPat receives requests to participate suffice to fund the Seller''s Upfront Price.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap;"><br></span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap;">Defensive and Strategic Licenses are offered, subject to availability, at the following prices:</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap;"><br></span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Cost Licensing:</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap;">During the Syndication period, Defensive and Strategic Licenses are offered at â€œCost Priceâ€ = Upfront Price divided by the total number of Defensive and Strategic Licenses bought by participating companies. &nbsp;Each Participant will pay directly to Seller an amount equal to the Cost Price multiplied by the number of Licenses it acquires. To avoid â€œpredationâ€, a Participant may acquire up to one Strategic License.&nbsp;</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap;"><br></span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap; text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Regular Licensing:</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap;">During the four (4) month period following the closing of the syndicate, Defensive and Strategic Licenses are offered at 50% markup on top of the Cost Price, i.e, at a price equal to 1.5 x Cost Price (â€œRegular Priceâ€).</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap;"><br></span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap; text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Risk Averse Licensing:</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap;">After the four (4) month Regular Licensing stage, Defensive and Strategic Licenses are offered at a premium price, equal to twice the Regular Price (â€œValidated Priceâ€), reflecting the marketâ€™s acknowledgment and validation of the Licenses and the underlying patents.</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap;"><br></span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 14.6667px; line-height: 20.24px; white-space: pre-wrap;">Companies participating in the Syndicate will receive from SynPat an amount equal to â…“ of all revenues from the Regular and Late Licensing, divided among the Participants pro-rata to the number licenses bought by each.</span></div>', '12345', '', 'admin@123', '', '12345', NULL, 'er.vivek2512@gmail.com', '123456', '', 'synpat@123', '12345', '', '12345', '', '12345', '', 'admin@123');
INSERT INTO `licenses` (`id`, `damage`, `license_number`, `serial_number`, `email_address`, `name`, `introduction`, `commitment_file`, `purchase_file`, `syndication_file`, `program_file`, `purchase_license`, `purchase_buy`, `purchase_buy_doc`, `purchase_file_doc`, `purchase_license_doc`, `cliamchart`, `prior_art`, `title`, `access_code`, `due_access_code`, `license_status`, `tabs_access_code`, `expiration_date`, `asking_price`, `portfolio_button_text`, `file_left`, `file_middle`, `file_right`, `file_four`, `file_five`, `file_six`, `file_seven`, `file_eight`, `file_nine`, `file_ten`, `file_eleven`, `file_twelve`, `portfolio_text`, `simulator_text`, `purchase_agreement`, `license_tab`, `buy_a_license_tab`, `due_diligence_tab`, `impact_tab`, `claim_chart_tab`, `prior_art_tab`, `program_tab`, `syndication_tab`, `damage_tab`, `store_tab`, `red_button`, `person_name`, `person_email`, `person_phone`, `person_picture`, `current_requesting_companies`, `program_policies_tab`, `program_policies_file`, `strategic_license_agreement`, `document_text`, `download_ppa`, `download_license`, `download_request`, `download_program_policies`, `active_button`, `deactive_tooltip`, `deactive_tooltip_regular`, `deactive_tooltip_risk`, `popup_text_participant`, `popup_text_regular`, `popup_text_risk`, `visibility`, `price_tab`, `portfolio_access_code`, `portfolio_email_address`, `comparables_admin_code`, `comparables_email_address`, `comparables_access_code`, `guide_for_comparables`, `tech_email_address`, `tech_access_code`, `legal_email_address`, `legal_access_code`, `pdf_access_code`, `pdf_email_address`, `images_access_code`, `images_email_address`, `illus_access_code`, `illus_email_address`, `master_passcode`) VALUES
(154, '', 'Sony', 93380210, '', 'Sony', '<p>1. Locate and select your company''s name from the list of invitees.</p>\r\n<p>2. Set the stages at which other companies might join the Progam,&nbsp;either as a Participant, a Regular Licensee, or a Late Licensee.</p>\r\n<p>3. Create different scenarios and see how each affects the cost of your license.</p>\r\n<p>4. Decide whether you would like to joint the Program and at which stage.&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '12345', '12345', 0, '12345', '', '0.0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<p><br></p>', '<div>The simulator below is aimed to assist you in figuring out at which of the three stages to acquire your license, once you decided to acquire one. &nbsp;It allows you to simulate scenarios under which several companies purchases licenses by participating in the crowdfunding syndicate, while others acquire their licenses later on as Regular Licensees, and some very conservative ones obtain their licenses as Late Licensees at any time after the Regular Licensing period.</div><div><br></div><div>Price differences:</div><div><ol><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Participants</span> pay a Cost Price, which is simply the Seller''s upfront price divided by the number of participants (SUP/NoP). Since Participants are entitled to receive from SynPat an equal share of 1/3 of all license fees received from licensees who did participate in the syndicate, i.e. from Regular Licensees, and Late Licensees, the "net cost" for each Participant is equal to the Cost Price minus its share in the future sales of licenses.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Regular Licensees</span> - companies that decide to acquire a license during the first 4 months after the close of the syndicate - pay a Regular Price, which is equal to 1.5 x Cost Price.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Late Licensees</span> pay a Validated Price - the price a company will pay if acquires the license at any time after the 4 months Regular Licensing period. The Validated price is equal to 2 x Regular Price.</span><br></li></ol></div><div><br></div><div>The table on the left hand side includes the list of companies that were invited to participate in the Syndicate and to acquire licenses at any later time. Using the Stage button next to each company''s name, you can create different scenarios and determine which companies will participate in the Syndicate, those who will buy licenses as Regular Licensees, and the laggards who will wait and acquire licenses only after many others will have bought the same licenses.</div><div><br></div><div>The three middle tables represent the three stages: Syndicate Participation, Regular Licensing, and Late Licensing, and will include the company names according to your selections and your estimated scenarios.</div><div><br></div><div>The first thing to begin with is to select the radio button next to your company''s name. Doing so will send your company to the first table of Participants. You can move it to different stages by changing the Select Stage button next to your company name.</div><div><br></div><div>Next, use the Select Stage buttons next to the companies you believe will buy a license to determine at which stage each will acquire its license. &nbsp;We believe that the more conservative a company is, the later it will acquire its license. The main reason for that could be the time it takes for such companies to assess the opportunity, decide, and react. Another reason could be the preferences of such companies to allow other companies to validate the quality of the license and the price, taking into consideration that higher price they would pay reflects the confidence they gain.</div>', '', '', '', 'The following information was diligently collected and prepared in effort to enable prospect Participants and Licensees to learn the scope of the inventions included in this portfolio, based on which make informed decisions whether or not to join this syndicate or to buy licenses at later times. We made special efforts to illustrate selected claims, element by element, which you can find under the Illustrations tab. Each mouse click will reveal additional claim element together with a corresponding illustration. This process is aimed to assist in quickly grasping the full scope of the entire claim as a whole. Please feel free to send us any inquiries relating the information provided here.', '<p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">This page is dedicated to demonstrating the impact of this patent portfolio. Impact is associated with the likelihood of a portfolio to generate a large amounts of license fees, which generally happens where the patents cover significant sources of revenues of large number of potential licensees. To learn about the impact of this patent portfolio we provided the following:</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Forward Citations:</span> Since both the applicant and the patent examiner must find and cite documents that may anticipate a claimed invention, the number of forward citations a patent receives, the citing entities, and the pattern of citing may point on the patent''s acknowledgement by others and sometimes even on its significance and relevance to others'' technologies.</span><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ''Open Sans'', arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px;">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Claim Charts:</span>&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 20.8px;">SynPat posted an order on ClaimCharts.info - a third party application - to produce claim charts reports. Via this online platform, subject matter experts were invited to study and prepare reports showing evidence of use, addressing each and every element of select claims from this portfolio. Posting of reports under the Claim Charts section is done automatically. Click on the patent(claim) number to see whether claim charts reports were submitted. If there are any, you may click the BUY button and purchase the reports using Paypal payment directly to the author of the report - the subject matter expert person or firm who prepared it. The prices and content of such reports are not the responsibility of SynPat.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Comparables:</span> Although SynPat offers licenses at three fixed prices: Cost Price = SUP/NoP, Regular Price = 1.5 x Cost Price, and Validated Price = 2 x Regular Price, in order to assist our customers in making informed decisions and properly evaluate this opportunity, it is useful to take into consideration alternative pricing. This section contains documents that can teach about the reasonable royalty rates that are relevant to this patent portfolio, as well as a sample of patent license agreements covering technologies with characteristics that are similar to the subject patents.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Royalty Rate Study:</span> S</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">ince patent licensing markets are known to be highly inefficient, and market transaction data is subject to significant error, the license fee appraisal process generally relies on multiple simultaneous approaches to value, with a judgemental reconciliation as the final step to arrive at the appraiser''s opinion. Thus, an Expert Royalty Rate Study was conducted specifically for this portfolio in an effort to identify the applicable range of reasonable royalty rates.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">License Fee Estimator:</span> After reviewing the comprables and studying the Expert Royalty Rate Study, you''ll be able to effectively use the License Fee Estimator to quickly and simply estimate your specific alternative cost of a license under this portfolio following these steps:</span></p><p></p><ol><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Apply your judgement to figure out the Maximum Royalty Rate and the Minimum Royalty Rate that could be applied to this portfolio, and plug them in the Estimator to calculate the </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: underline;">average</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> royalty rate.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Use the handle bar to adjust the average royalty rate in order to take into consideration and reflect specific circumstances that require a higher or lower rate, in order to obtain the </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; text-decoration: underline;">reasonable</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> royalty rate.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Enter your average addressable sales that might be found covered by the parent portfolio.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Enter the relevant number of years of an applicable license.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Calculate your expected alternative license fee.</span><br></li></ol><p></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p>', '<p>The following content is aimed to demonstrate the quality of this portfolio. We use the term quality to relate to the likelihood of a licensing campaign to sustain challenges. The materials below contains information on the existence of licenses granted under this portfolio, and if there are any - to the nature of such licenses. Most of the information in this page is not publicly available, and therefore was provided by the seller. This page also contains information about the chain of title, and addresses irregularities or missing items that might make the potentially transferred title questionable or unclear. In some cases, when needed, we provided the agreements showing assignments along the life of the patents. We also included declarations and information by the seller with regard to the involvement and rights of third parties such as universities and governmental agencies that might pose challenges and hardship in future licensing. Involvement of the inventors or the seller in industry standard activities and the existence of potential commitments to different SSO to FRAND terms licensing is also addressed. Next are data relating to collateral by creditors and other third parties that might encumber the portfolio and the ability to license it. We also included reports from patent offices relating to payment of maintenance fees, and other activities that might affect a the licensing power. Information on backward citations is provided as well, and is aimed to show whether and to what extent the inventor and examiner addressed prior arts.</p><p>SynPat posted an order on ClaimCharts.info - a third party application - to produce prior art reports. Via this online platform, subject matter experts were invited to study and prepare reports showing invalidating prior art, addressing each and every element of select claims from this portfolio. Posting of reports under the Prior Art section is done automatically. Click on the patent(claim) number to see whether prior art reports were submitted. If there are any, you may click the BUY button and purchase the reports using Paypal payment directly to the author of the report - the subject matter expert person or firm who prepared it. The prices and content of such reports are not the responsibility of SynPat.</p>', '', '', '<div><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">The Syndication Process:</span></div><div><br></div><div>The Syndication Process is explained and illustrated below:</div><div><ol><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">We begin with the execution of a Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) between a patent seller and SynPat, which defines the list of patents to be acquired by SynPat, Sellerâ€™s Upfront Price (SUP), and the deadline for closing the syndicate, which is generally 100 days from the PPA''s effective date.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">SynPat begins an extensive due diligence during which it invite operating companies to participate in crowdfunding the SUP. The invitations to participate include a copy of the PPA, a draft Patent License Agreement (PLA) under which SynPat will grant the license under the acquired patent portfolio to interested customers, a draft Strategic License under interested customers will be able to acquire the exclusive rights to license the acquired patents to a designated company of its choice (provided such a company has not yet purchased a license), a Request to Participate form, which which interested customers can submit to SynPat their commitments to participate in the syndicate, and finally, a copy of the program terms - a document that explains the SynPat licensing stages.&nbsp;</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Companies that wish to participate in the syndicate must send to SynPat a Request to Participate, stating the maximum license fee they commit to pay. Clicking the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page would allow you to submit your executed Request to Participate together with any comments, requests, or instructions to SynPat. Upon doing that, you''ll receive an immediate confirmation on receiving your request. Please keep in mind that your participation is secured and you will be considered a participant when SynPat receives commitments from interested companies, sufficient to equally crowdfund the SUP, and your committed amount is equal or greater than the SUP divided by the number of participating companies (NoP).</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Upon receiving Requests to Participate from interested companies, sufficient to equally crowdfund the SUP, SynPat will notify the Seller of the successful syndicate formation. The notice to Seller effectuates the licenses to all the participants. Note that licenses to participants become effective before the fee is paid by them.&nbsp;</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Next, SynPat sends to all participants a Payment Notice stating the exact participation fee to be paid (= SUP/NoP).</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Participants then counter execute the License Agreement, and pay their participation fee within seven calendar days. Please note that payments are to be made directly to the Sellerâ€™s bank account, as stated in the PPA and the PLA.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Upon full payment of the SUP to the Seller, the title to the acquired patents is assigned to SynPat. Note that a failure to pay a participation fee by any participant does not affect the validity of your licenses. Rest assured that your license is in full effect upon your receiving a Payment Notice from SynPat.</span><br></li></ol></div>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<div>This page contains the following documents and functionalities:</div><div><br></div><div><span style="transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">PURCHASE AGREEMENT</span>&nbsp;- a copy of the actual Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) as executed between the seller of this patent portfolio and SynPat as a buyer. This agreement is subject to confidentiality terms, and the parties agreed to expose the agreement to you as a potential Participant or a Licensee, but not to others. Please respect the parties'' agreement and kindly refrain from disclosing it to third parties.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">NON-EXCLUSIVE LICENSE</span>&nbsp;- a draft of SynPat standard Patent License Agreement. This agreement is applicable to all licensees whether they acquire their licenses as Participants, Regular Licensees, or Late Licensees. The difference is in the prices paid in exchange for the non-exclusive license. Participants pay the Cost Price = SUP/NoP and are entitled <span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">to receive from SynPat an equal share of 1/3 of all license fees received from licensees who did participate in the syndicate. Regular Licensees'' pay the Regular Price = 1.5 x Cost Price, and Late Licensees pay the Validated Price - 2 x Regular Price.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">STRATEGIC LICENSE</span>&nbsp;- a draft of SynPat standard Strategic License Agreement (SLA) in case you would like to acquire from SynPat the rights to license (and enforce this patent portfolio on) a designated third party, perhaps one of your competitors. While the price of a regular non-exclusive license under the PLA changes from Cost Price to Regular Price and then to Validated Price, the price of Strategic License is always a Regular Price regardless of the time it is purchased.</div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">REQUEST TO PARTICIPATE</span><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">&nbsp;- the Request to Participate (RTP) form is used to by companies to inform SynPat about their intention to participate in the syndicate to crowdfund the SUP. To use this form, download and print it, fill it in and execute it, then use the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page to upload and submit it to SynPat. Please note that your participation fee will be determined according to the formula: Seller''s Asking Price / Number of Participants. &nbsp;The maximum amount that you state on your RTP is for SynPat to figure out whether your request is suffice for participation taking into consideration the requsts submitted by others. Ultimately, you, like all all other Participants will pay the same amount: Cost Price = SUP/NoP.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">PROGRAM</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">&nbsp;- The SynPat Program Procedure and Policies (PPP) describes in details the unique licensing approach offered by SynPat.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><br></span></div><div><span style="color: inherit; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">DOWNLOAD / UPLOAD</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">&nbsp;- From this page customers can download the above documents. If you would like to suggest revisions to the language of any of the documents you may do so by downloading them, making your tracked edits and submitting them back to SynPat using the form on this page.</span></div>', '', '', '', '', 1, 'The Syndication stage of this portfolio has completed. At this time, you may acquire a Regular License', 'The Syndication stage for this portfolio is still open, and you may acquire a license as a Participant. Regular Licenses will be available upon a successful syndication.', 'Risk Averse Licenses will be available upon completion of both the Syndication and the Regular Licensing stages.', '<p>Thank you for your interest in participating in this syndicate. Please feel free to contact me with any questions. As you may know, the participation fee is calculated by dividing the Seller''s Upfront Price by the number of Participants. Please download the Request to Participate from the Documents tab, fill it out and submit it to SynPat, using this form.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Regular License under this portfoio. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent Licensee Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and submit it to SynPat using this form. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 50% higher than the price each Participant paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired (as a Strategic License) by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Validated License under this patent portfoio. We call it a Validated License because so many other licensees have validated this patent portfolio since it was introduced by SynPat. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent License Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and upload it using the button below. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 100% higher than the amount each Regular Licensee paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', 0, NULL, '12345', '', 'admin@123', '', '12345', NULL, '', '12345', NULL, '12345', '12345', '', '12345', '', '12345', '', 'admin@123'),
(155, '', 'Beyond_Edison', 90385864, '', 'Beyond Edison', '<p>1. Locate and select your company''s name from the list of invitees.</p>\r\n<p>2. Set the stages at which other companies might join the Progam,&nbsp;either as a Participant, a Regular Licensee, or a Late Licensee.</p>\r\n<p>3. Create different scenarios and see how each affects the cost of your license.</p>\r\n<p>4. Decide whether you would like to joint the Program and at which stage.&nbsp;</p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '12345', '12345', 0, '12345', '', '0.0', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<p><br></p>', '<div>The simulator below is aimed to assist you in figuring out at which of the three stages to acquire your license, once you decided to acquire one. &nbsp;It allows you to simulate scenarios under which several companies purchases licenses by participating in the crowdfunding syndicate, while others acquire their licenses later on as Regular Licensees, and some very conservative ones obtain their licenses as Late Licensees at any time after the Regular Licensing period.</div><div><br></div><div>Price differences:</div><div><ol><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Participants</span> pay a Cost Price, which is simply the Seller''s upfront price divided by the number of participants (SUP/NoP). Since Participants are entitled to receive from SynPat an equal share of 1/3 of all license fees received from licensees who did participate in the syndicate, i.e. from Regular Licensees, and Late Licensees, the "net cost" for each Participant is equal to the Cost Price minus its share in the future sales of licenses.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Regular Licensees</span> - companies that decide to acquire a license during the first 4 months after the close of the syndicate - pay a Regular Price, which is equal to 1.5 x Cost Price.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Late Licensees</span> pay a Validated Price - the price a company will pay if acquires the license at any time after the 4 months Regular Licensing period. The Validated price is equal to 2 x Regular Price.</span><br></li></ol></div><div><br></div><div>The table on the left hand side includes the list of companies that were invited to participate in the Syndicate and to acquire licenses at any later time. Using the Stage button next to each company''s name, you can create different scenarios and determine which companies will participate in the Syndicate, those who will buy licenses as Regular Licensees, and the laggards who will wait and acquire licenses only after many others will have bought the same licenses.</div><div><br></div><div>The three middle tables represent the three stages: Syndicate Participation, Regular Licensing, and Late Licensing, and will include the company names according to your selections and your estimated scenarios.</div><div><br></div><div>The first thing to begin with is to select the radio button next to your company''s name. Doing so will send your company to the first table of Participants. You can move it to different stages by changing the Select Stage button next to your company name.</div><div><br></div><div>Next, use the Select Stage buttons next to the companies you believe will buy a license to determine at which stage each will acquire its license. &nbsp;We believe that the more conservative a company is, the later it will acquire its license. The main reason for that could be the time it takes for such companies to assess the opportunity, decide, and react. Another reason could be the preferences of such companies to allow other companies to validate the quality of the license and the price, taking into consideration that higher price they would pay reflects the confidence they gain.</div>', '', '', '', 'The following information was diligently collected and prepared in effort to enable prospect Participants and Licensees to learn the scope of the inventions included in this portfolio, based on which make informed decisions whether or not to join this syndicate or to buy licenses at later times. We made special efforts to illustrate selected claims, element by element, which you can find under the Illustrations tab. Each mouse click will reveal additional claim element together with a corresponding illustration. This process is aimed to assist in quickly grasping the full scope of the entire claim as a whole. Please feel free to send us any inquiries relating the information provided here.', '<p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">This page is dedicated to demonstrating the impact of this patent portfolio. Impact is associated with the likelihood of a portfolio to generate a large amounts of license fees, which generally happens where the patents cover significant sources of revenues of large number of potential licensees. To learn about the impact of this patent portfolio we provided the following:</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">Forward Citations:</span> Since both the applicant and the patent examiner must find and cite documents that may anticipate a claimed invention, the number of forward citations a patent receives, the citing entities, and the pattern of citing may point on the patent''s acknowledgement by others and sometimes even on its significance and relevance to others'' technologies.</span><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: ''Open Sans'', arial, sans-serif; line-height: 19.5px;">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="t