s-serif; line-height: 20px;">Enter your average addressable sales that might be found covered by the parent portfolio.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Enter the relevant number of years of an applicable license.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Calculate your expected alternative license fee.</span><br></li></ol><p></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><br></span></p>', '<p>The following content is aimed to demonstrate the quality of this portfolio. We use the term quality to relate to the likelihood of a licensing campaign to sustain challenges. The materials below contains information on the existence of licenses granted under this portfolio, and if there are any - to the nature of such licenses. Most of the information in this page is not publicly available, and therefore was provided by the seller. This page also contains information about the chain of title, and addresses irregularities or missing items that might make the potentially transferred title questionable or unclear. In some cases, when needed, we provided the agreements showing assignments along the life of the patents. We also included declarations and information by the seller with regard to the involvement and rights of third parties such as universities and governmental agencies that might pose challenges and hardship in future licensing. Involvement of the inventors or the seller in industry standard activities and the existence of potential commitments to different SSO to FRAND terms licensing is also addressed. Next are data relating to collateral by creditors and other third parties that might encumber the portfolio and the ability to license it. We also included reports from patent offices relating to payment of maintenance fees, and other activities that might affect a the licensing power. Information on backward citations is provided as well, and is aimed to show whether and to what extent the inventor and examiner addressed prior arts.</p><p>SynPat posted an order on ClaimCharts.info - a third party application - to produce prior art reports. Via this online platform, subject matter experts were invited to study and prepare reports showing invalidating prior art, addressing each and every element of select claims from this portfolio. Posting of reports under the Prior Art section is done automatically. Click on the patent(claim) number to see whether prior art reports were submitted. If there are any, you may click the BUY button and purchase the reports using Paypal payment directly to the author of the report - the subject matter expert person or firm who prepared it. The prices and content of such reports are not the responsibility of SynPat.</p>', '', '', '<div><span style="text-decoration: underline; font-weight: bold;">The Syndication Process:</span></div><div><br></div><div>The Syndication Process is explained and illustrated below:</div><div><ol><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">We begin with the execution of a Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) between a patent seller and SynPat, which defines the list of patents to be acquired by SynPat, Sellerâ€™s Upfront Price (SUP), and the deadline for closing the syndicate, which is generally 100 days from the PPA''s effective date.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">SynPat begins an extensive due diligence during which it invite operating companies to participate in crowdfunding the SUP. The invitations to participate include a copy of the PPA, a draft Patent License Agreement (PLA) under which SynPat will grant the license under the acquired patent portfolio to interested customers, a draft Strategic License under interested customers will be able to acquire the exclusive rights to license the acquired patents to a designated company of its choice (provided such a company has not yet purchased a license), a Request to Participate form, which which interested customers can submit to SynPat their commitments to participate in the syndicate, and finally, a copy of the program terms - a document that explains the SynPat licensing stages.&nbsp;</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Companies that wish to participate in the syndicate must send to SynPat a Request to Participate, stating the maximum license fee they commit to pay. Clicking the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page would allow you to submit your executed Request to Participate together with any comments, requests, or instructions to SynPat. Upon doing that, you''ll receive an immediate confirmation on receiving your request. Please keep in mind that your participation is secured and you will be considered a participant when SynPat receives commitments from interested companies, sufficient to equally crowdfund the SUP, and your committed amount is equal or greater than the SUP divided by the number of participating companies (NoP).</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Upon receiving Requests to Participate from interested companies, sufficient to equally crowdfund the SUP, SynPat will notify the Seller of the successful syndicate formation. The notice to Seller effectuates the licenses to all the participants. Note that licenses to participants become effective before the fee is paid by them.&nbsp;</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Next, SynPat sends to all participants a Payment Notice stating the exact participation fee to be paid (= SUP/NoP).</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Participants then counter execute the License Agreement, and pay their participation fee within seven calendar days. Please note that payments are to be made directly to the Sellerâ€™s bank account, as stated in the PPA and the PLA.</span><br></li><li class="ms-hover"><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Upon full payment of the SUP to the Seller, the title to the acquired patents is assigned to SynPat. Note that a failure to pay a participation fee by any participant does not affect the validity of your licenses. Rest assured that your license is in full effect upon your receiving a Payment Notice from SynPat.</span><br></li></ol></div>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<div>This page contains the following documents and functionalities:</div><div><br></div><div><span style="transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; color: inherit; text-decoration: underline;">PURCHASE AGREEMENT</span>&nbsp;- a copy of the actual Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) as executed between the seller of this patent portfolio and SynPat as a buyer. This agreement is subject to confidentiality terms, and the parties agreed to expose the agreement to you as a potential Participant or a Licensee, but not to others. Please respect the parties'' agreement and kindly refrain from disclosing it to third parties.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">NON-EXCLUSIVE LICENSE</span>&nbsp;- a draft of SynPat standard Patent License Agreement. This agreement is applicable to all licensees whether they acquire their licenses as Participants, Regular Licensees, or Late Licensees. The difference is in the prices paid in exchange for the non-exclusive license. Participants pay the Cost Price = SUP/NoP and are entitled <span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">to receive from SynPat an equal share of 1/3 of all license fees received from licensees who did participate in the syndicate. Regular Licensees'' pay the Regular Price = 1.5 x Cost Price, and Late Licensees pay the Validated Price - 2 x Regular Price.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">STRATEGIC LICENSE</span>&nbsp;- a draft of SynPat standard Strategic License Agreement (SLA) in case you would like to acquire from SynPat the rights to license (and enforce this patent portfolio on) a designated third party, perhaps one of your competitors. While the price of a regular non-exclusive license under the PLA changes from Cost Price to Regular Price and then to Validated Price, the price of Strategic License is always a Regular Price regardless of the time it is purchased.</div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">REQUEST TO PARTICIPATE</span><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">&nbsp;- the Request to Participate (RTP) form is used to by companies to inform SynPat about their intention to participate in the syndicate to crowdfund the SUP. To use this form, download and print it, fill it in and execute it, then use the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page to upload and submit it to SynPat. Please note that your participation fee will be determined according to the formula: Seller''s Asking Price / Number of Participants. &nbsp;The maximum amount that you state on your RTP is for SynPat to figure out whether your request is suffice for participation taking into consideration the requsts submitted by others. Ultimately, you, like all all other Participants will pay the same amount: Cost Price = SUP/NoP.</span></div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: inherit; transition-duration: initial; transition-timing-function: initial; transition-property: none; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">PROGRAM</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">&nbsp;- The SynPat Program Procedure and Policies (PPP) describes in details the unique licensing approach offered by SynPat.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><br></span></div><div><span style="color: inherit; font-size: 14px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 20px; text-align: center; text-decoration: underline;">DOWNLOAD / UPLOAD</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">&nbsp;- From this page customers can download the above documents. If you would like to suggest revisions to the language of any of the documents you may do so by downloading them, making your tracked edits and submitting them back to SynPat using the form on this page.</span></div>', '', '', '', '', 1, 'The Syndication stage of this portfolio has completed. At this time, you may acquire a Regular License', 'The Syndication stage for this portfolio is still open, and you may acquire a license as a Participant. Regular Licenses will be available upon a successful syndication.', 'Risk Averse Licenses will be available upon completion of both the Syndication and the Regular Licensing stages.', '<p>Thank you for your interest in participating in this syndicate. Please feel free to contact me with any questions. As you may know, the participation fee is calculated by dividing the Seller''s Upfront Price by the number of Participants. Please download the Request to Participate from the Documents tab, fill it out and submit it to SynPat, using this form.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Regular License under this portfoio. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent Licensee Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and submit it to SynPat using this form. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 50% higher than the price each Participant paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired (as a Strategic License) by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Validated License under this patent portfoio. We call it a Validated License because so many other licensees have validated this patent portfolio since it was introduced by SynPat. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent License Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and upload it using the button below. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 100% higher than the amount each Regular Licensee paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', 0, NULL, '12345', '', 'admin@123', '', '12345', NULL, '', '12345', NULL, '12345', '12345', '', '12345', '', '12345', '', 'admin@123');
