(156, '', 'Metro_Enterprises', 85865, 'simon@dynaipdeals.com', 'Metro Enterprises', '<p>1. Locate and select your company''s name from the list of invitees.</p>\r\n<p>2. Set the stages at which other companies might join the Progam,&nbsp;either as a Participant, a Regular Licensee, or a Late Licensee.</p>\r\n<p>3. Create different scenarios and see how each affects the cost of your license.</p>\r\n<p>4. Decide whether you would like to joint the Program and at which stage.&nbsp;</p>', '', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Q1MuGCt-0kn8FqpX3DA1fRDaYIRBIcrd3uVWtvH9WsI/edit', '', '', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1zXGMexeBRhIczzB-zhibmEKGV_NE_h77fcxpd9gwGBw/edit?usp=drivesdk', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1xA_lN1lGSXeKEqHVv9oIySRV2mPljYTHj2Azgo7mGGY/edit?usp=drivesdk', '', '', '', '<iframe src="http://claimcharts.info/index.php/component/survey/?tmpl=component&task=customer.generateClientRequest&client_id=Metro&pr=2" width="100%" height="680" frameborder="0" scrolling="yes"></iframe>', '', '', '12345', 'metro', 0, '12345', '08/01/2016', '0.6', '', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B-7JHq4pougDMXpJS0dOV1pBa1k', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B-7JHq4pougDSUJuZ2ZCM2I4aDQ', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFdU1oa3dwcURIZ0k', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B-7JHq4pougDWXJDUVk0Z2NzTEk', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFYWNLclZWbnBGdVk', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFYWxLU2cwYkRrQWM', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFU0QtZmhxQW9vT0E', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B-7JHq4pougDU0ZzRXVCY0MwYk0', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B-7JHq4pougDYk5XQlFISTBjaVE', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFU0QtZmhxQW9vT0E', '', '', '<p>SynPat decided to acquire this patent portfolio since it covers many potential licensees who could benefit from obtaining licenses that are unavailable otherwise. This portfolio is directed to <span style="font-weight: bold;">marketing systems known as "pay-per-call" - mechanisms that allow a telephone lead source to sell the lead to the marketer who is willing to pay the highest price for the lead.</span> &nbsp;Marketers bid against one another for a per-call charge. When a lead source receives a telephone call from a customer the telephone call is routed to the highest bidder.&nbsp;In case the highest bidder does not answer the call within a predetermined number of rings, the call is re-routed to the next highest bidder, and the service provider who answers the call is charged.</p><p><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">Companies that provide services that&nbsp;rout customers'' calls to one of many interested marketers based on the price the marketers are interested to pay for the lead may find this opportunity to acquire non-exclusive as well as strategic licenses appealing.</span></p><p><span style="line-height: 1.6em; font-weight: bold;">The priority date of this portfolio is December 22, 2004</span><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">. &nbsp;The portfolio is comprised of three US patents, and several expired Japanese, Canadian, and Australian patents.</span></p><p><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">The expected number of licensees as they spread along the different segments of the market together with the information provided in this docket support a rational decision to invest and participate in the effort to crowdfund the acquisition of this portfolio, and to acquire non-exclusive and strategic licenses.</span></p><p><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">So long as SynPat holds a portfolio of patents, any operating company may submit to SynPat a request to acquire from SynPat either a </span><span style="line-height: 1.6em; font-weight: bold;">Defensive License</span><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">, a </span><span style="line-height: 1.6em; font-weight: bold;">Strategic License</span><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">, or both.</span></p><p><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">A Defensive License is a paid up non-exclusive license under the acquired patent portfolio. A Strategic License provides its buyer the right to license any other operating company of its choice (â€œDesignated Third Partyâ€).</span></p><p><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">A request to acquire a license is always subject to availability. &nbsp;For example, a request by Company A to acquire a Strategic License that would allow it to exclusively license Company B must arrive to SynPat before a similar request from Company C, or a request from Company B to acquire a Defensive License is received by SynPat. Also, a request by Company B to acquire a Defensive License must arrive to SynPat before a request from Company A to acquire a Strategic License, which would allow it to exclusively license Company B, is received by SynPat.</span></p><p><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">In guiding its actions, SynPat will use the date and time of actual receipt of any request, and unless the date and time of the request </span><span style="line-height: 1.6em;"></span><gs id="d85d47cf-647e-417b-b865-b41f1a37dad2" ginger_software_uiphraseguid="b906d1b4-262a-44f0-acd8-c3da01edd32e" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark"><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">to&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 1.6em;">acquire</span></gs><span style="line-height: 1.6em;"></span><span style="line-height: 1.6em;"></span><span style="line-height: 1.6em;"> the right to license a Designated Third Party can be clearly shown to have been received by SynPat prior to a request for a Defensive License by the Designated Third Party, SynPat will honor the request of the Designated Third Party.</span></p>', '<div><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">The simulator below is aimed to assist you in figuring out the stage at which to acquire your license. &nbsp;It allows you to simulate scenarios under which several companies purchase licenses by participating in the crowdfunding syndicate, while others acquire their licenses later on as Regular Licensees, and some very conservative ones obtain their licenses as Late Licensees.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 18.5714px; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Structure:</span></div><blockquote style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><div><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">The <span style="font-weight: bold;">Invitees Table</span>&nbsp;is the table on the left hand side lists the companies that were invited to participate in the Syndicate and to acquire licenses at any later time. Using the Stage button next to each company''s name, you can create different scenarios selecting the companies that will participate in the Syndicate, those who will buy licenses as Regular Licensees, and the laggards who will wait and acquire licenses only after many others do the same.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">The <span style="font-weight: bold;">Participants Table</span>, the <span style="font-weight: bold;">Regular Licensees Table</span>, and the <span style="font-weight: bold;">Late Licensees Table</span>&nbsp;are those in the middle representing the three stages: Syndicate Participation, Regular Licensing, and Late Licensing, and will include the company names according to your scenarios.</span></div></blockquote><div><span style="line-height: 18.5714px; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Operation:</span></div><blockquote style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><div><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">Start by locating your company in the Invitees Table and clicking the radio button next to its name. Note that your company was added to the Participants Table. You can move your company to the Regular Licensees Table or the Late Licensees Table by changing the Select Stage button next to its name in the Invitees Table.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">Next, estimate which other companies will acquire licenses (either Defensive, Strategic or both) and use the Select Stage buttons next to their names to set the stages at which they will do that. It is believed that the more conservative a company is the longer it would take it to executes its will, as they are slower in assessing the opportunity, deciding, and reacting. Or because they strategically allow other companies to validate the quality of the license. Although due to the price differences and the strategic advantages in buying early, there are arguments that support the exact opposite view.</span></div></blockquote><div><span style="line-height: 18.5714px; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Price differences:</span></div><blockquote style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><div><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">Participants pay a <span style="font-weight: bold;">Cost Price</span>* = Seller''s Upfront Price / Number of licenses bought by Participants.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">Regular Licensees pay <span style="font-weight: bold;">Regular Price</span> = &nbsp;1.5 * Regular Price &nbsp; &nbsp;(available to companies that decide to acquire a license during the first 4 months after the close of the syndicate)</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">Late Licensees pay <span style="font-weight: bold;">Validated Price</span> = 2 * Regular Price &nbsp; &nbsp;(available to companies that decide to acquire a license any time after the Regular Licensing stage)</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">* Since Participants receive back from SynPat one third (1/3) of all license fees received from licensees who did participate in the syndicate, i.e. from Regular Licensees, and Late Licensees, the net cost per license is much smaller and can negative.</span></div></blockquote>', '', '', '', '<div>The following information was diligently collected and prepared in an effort to enable prospect Participants and Licensees to learn the scope of the inventions included in this portfolio, and <span style="font-weight: bold;">make informed decisions</span> whether to join this syndicate or to buy licenses at a later time. We made special efforts to illustrate selected claims, element by element, which you can find under the Illustrations tab. Each mouse click will reveal an additional claim element together with a corresponding illustration.</div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">This process is aimed to assist in quickly grasping the full scope of the entire claim as a whole. </span><gs id="0578e4c1-4e77-4377-862f-44f0250f5964" ginger_software_uiphraseguid="c7f1bec0-6358-4fee-bf05-2fd7f6187fee" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark" style="line-height: 1.42857;"><gs id="ab435c04-a031-44ae-8413-59204e4170b6" ginger_software_uiphraseguid="d5b31bd3-8de3-4264-a901-0228929480bd" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark">P</gs></gs><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">lease feel free to send us any inquiries relating to the information provided here.</span></div>', '<div><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">This page is dedicated to demonstrating the impact of this patent portfolio. The term ''impact'' is associated with the likelihood of a portfolio to generate a large amounts of license fees, which generally happens where the patents cover significant sources of revenues of large number of potential licensees. To learn about the impact of this patent portfolio, you may review the following:</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; font-weight: bold;">Claim</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"> Charts:</span> SynPat posts orders on ClaimCharts.info - a third party application - to produce claim </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">chart</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> reports. Via this online platform, subject matter experts were invited to study and prepare reports showing evidence of use, addressing each and every element of select claims from this portfolio. Posting of reports under the Claim Charts section is done automatically. Click on the patent</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> (</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">claim) number to see whether claim </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">chart</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> reports were submitted. If there are any, you may click the BUY button and purchase the reports using </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">PayPal</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> payment directly to the author of the report - the subject matter expert person or firm who prepared it. The prices and content of such reports are not the responsibility of SynPat.</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px; font-weight: bold;">Comparables</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">:</span>&nbsp;SynPat offers licenses at fixed </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">prices, which are unrelated to risk or exposure, yet&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">our customers may better <span style="font-weight: bold;">evaluate this opportunity</span>&nbsp;take into consideration alternative pricing. This section contains documents that can teach about the reasonable royalty rates that are relevant to this patent portfolio, as well as a sample of patent license agreements covering </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">the technologies</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> with characteristics that are similar to the subject patents.</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Royalty Rate Study:</span> Since patent licensing markets are known to be highly inefficient, and market transaction data is subject to significant error, the license </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">fee appraisal</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> process generally relies on multiple simultaneous approaches to value, with a </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">judgmental</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> reconciliation as the final step to arrive at the appraiser''s opinion. Thus, an Expert Royalty Rate Study was conducted specifically for this portfolio in an effort to identify the applicable range of reasonable royalty rates.</span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">License Fee Estimator:</span> After reviewing the </span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">comprables</span><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"> and studying the Expert Royalty Rate Study, you''ll be able to effectively use the License Fee Estimator to quickly and simply estimate your specific alternative cost of a license under this portfolio following these steps:</span></div><div><ol><ol><li><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Apply your judgement to figure out the Maximum Royalty Rate and the Minimum Royalty Rate that could be applied to this portfolio, and plug them in the Estimator to calculate the average royalty rate.</span></li><li><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Use the handle bar to adjust the average royalty rate in order to take into consideration and reflect specific circumstances that require a higher or lower rate, in order to obtain the reasonable royalty rate.</span></li><li><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Enter your average addressable sales that might be found covered by the patent portfolio.</span></li><li><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Enter the relevant number of years of an applicable license.</span></li><li><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;">Calculate your expected alternative license fee.</span></li></ol></ol><span style="color: rgb(54, 54, 54); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 20px;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Forward Citations:</span> Since both the applicant and the patent examiner must find and cite documents that may anticipate a claimed invention, the number of forward citations a patent receives, the citing entities, and the pattern of citations may point on the patent''s acknowledgement by others and sometimes even on its significance and relevance to others'' technologies.</span><br></div>', '<p>The following content is aimed to demonstrate the quality of this portfolio. The term ''quality'' relates to the likelihood of a licensing campaign to <span style="font-weight: bold;">sustain challenges</span>. The information on this page, most of which was provided by the seller, relates to <span style="font-weight: bold;">existing licenses</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">chains of title</span>, and addresses irregularities or missing items that might make the potentially transferred title questionable or unclear. In some cases, when needed, the agreements showing <span style="font-weight: bold;">assignments along the life of the patents</span> were also provided, as well as seller''s declarations and statement with regard to involvement and<span style="font-weight: bold;"> third party''s rights</span> such as universities and governmental agencies that might pose challenges and hardship in future licensing.&nbsp;</p><p>Involvement of the inventors or the seller in<span style="font-weight: bold;"> industry standardization activities</span> and the existence of potential commitments to different SSO on FRAND term licensing is also addressed as well as questions relating to <span style="font-weight: bold;">collaterals by creditors and other third parties'' rights</span> that might encumber the portfolio and the ability to license it. Direct evidence on <span style="font-weight: bold;">maintenance fees</span>, and certain events included among the <span style="font-weight: bold;">prosecution activities</span>, which might affect a the licensing power of this portfolio are also provided. <span style="font-weight: bold;">Backward citations</span> by third parties was brought to show whether and to what extent the inventor and examiner addressed prior art.</p><p>SynPat generally post orders on ClaimCharts.info - a third party application - to produce <span style="font-weight: bold;">prior art reports</span>. Via this online platform, subject matter experts were invited to study and prepare reports showing invalidating prior art, addressing each and every element of select claims from this portfolio. Posting of reports under the Prior Art section is done automatically. Click on the patent claim number to see whether prior art reports were submitted. If there are any, you may click the BUY button and purchase the reports using PayPal payment directly to the author of the report - the subject matter expert person or firm who prepared it. The prices and content of these reports are not the responsibility of SynPat.</p>', '', '', '<div style=""><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Rather than reaching out to financial resources to fund the Upfront Price, SynPat creates an ad-hoc syndicate and offers relevant operating companies to share the Upfront Price in exchange for non-exclusive licenses and Strategic Licenses under the acquired patents. In addition to buying licenses, Participants are also entitled to pro-rata shares in â…“ of all SynPatâ€™s revenues from its Open Licensing Program.</span><br><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">The Syndication Process is explained and illustrated below:</span><br><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">The program begins with the execution of a Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) between a patent seller and SynPat, according to which SynPat acquires the lists of patents in consideration of the Sellerâ€™s Upfront Price (SUP) and 1/3 of SynPat''s revenues. The PPA also sets the deadline for closing the syndicate and making the payment of the SUP to the seller.</span><br><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">SynPat begins an extensive due diligence during which it creates this online Docket and invites interested operating companies to review this Docket and participate in crowdfunding the SUP. The Documents section of this online Docket includes the following:</span></div><blockquote style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><div style=""><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">A copy of the<span style="font-weight: bold;"> PPA</span>.</span></div><div style=""><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">A draft <span style="font-weight: bold;">Patent License Agreement</span> (PLA) to be executed between SynPat and companies interested in acquiring non-exclusive licenses under the acquired patents.</span></div><div style=""><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">A draft <span style="font-weight: bold;">Strategic License Agreement</span> (SLA) to be executed between SynPat and companies interested in acquiring exclusive rights to license the acquired patents to a designated company (Targets) of their choice (provided such a Target has not yet purchased a non-exclusive licence).</span></div><div style=""><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">A <span style="font-weight: bold;">Request to Participate</span> form (RtP) for interested to send their commitments to SynPat to p</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">articipate in the syndicate.</span></div><div style=""><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">A copy of the <span style="font-weight: bold;">Program</span> terms - a document that explains the SynPat licensing stages.</span></div></blockquote><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Companies that wish to participate in the syndicate </span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">should c</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">lick </span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">&nbsp;and upload their executed Request to Participate, stating the maximum license fee they commit to pay. You''ll receive an automatic confirmation for the date and time of submittal.</span><br><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Upon receiving Requests to Participate from interested companies, sufficient to equally crowdfund the SUP, SynPat will notify the Seller of the successful syndicate formation, effectuating the licenses to all the participants. Note that licenses to participants become effective before the fee is paid by them.</span><br><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Next, SynPat sends to all participants a Payment Notice stating the exact participation fee to be paid (= SUP/NoP).</span><br><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Participants then execute the License Agreement, and pay their participation fee within seven calendar days. Please note that payments are to be made directly to the Sellerâ€™s bank account, as stated in the PPA and the PLA.</span><br><span style="line-height: 18.5714px; font-weight: bold;">Your license&nbsp;is in full effect upon your receiving a Payment Notice from SynPat, and&nbsp;is valid regardless of other participant''s failure to pay its fee.</span></div>', '', '', '', 'Uzi Aloush', 'uzi@synpat.com', '+1-415-803-8813', 'https://www.googledrive.com/host/0B61I0m5ybHrFTERnXzV4Qm5CWGs', '', '', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/18AmX-MHoWWnPms4cvVJqAlb4UtztbRe3utPO62GkFlU/edit?usp=drivesdk', 'https://docs.google.com/document/d/1c5s9VXbCnFERsMgrz46VcjsJ0x5oMUymq5B6EUGSBlY/edit?usp=drivesdk', '<div>This page contains the following documents and functionalities:</div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Purchase Agreement</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"> - a copy of the actual Patent Purchase Agreement (PPA) as executed between the seller of this patent portfolio and SynPat as a buyer. This agreement is subject to confidentiality terms, and the parties agreed to expose the agreement to you as a potential Participant or a Licensee, but not to others. Please respect the parties'' agreement and kindly refrain from disclosing it to third parties.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Non-Exclusive License</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"> - a draft of SynPat standard Patent License Agreement. This agreement is applicable to all licensees whether they acquire their licenses as Participants, Regular Licensees, or Late Licensees. The difference is in the prices paid in exchange for the non-exclusive license. Participants pay the Cost Price = SUP/NoP and are entitled to receive from SynPat an equal share of 1/3 of all license fees received from licensees who did participate in the syndicate. Regular Licensees'' pay the Regular Price = 1.5 x </span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><gs id="5ffa9647-3511-439e-8df8-9f8c471ab86f" ginger_software_uiphraseguid="c3270aa7-fab4-47bb-9a88-c70a6593e334" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark">Cost Price</gs></span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">, and Late Licensees pay the Validated Price - 2 x Regular Price.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Strategic License</span> - a draft of SynPat standard Strategic License Agreement (SLA) in case you would like to acquire from SynPat the rights to license (and enforce this patent portfolio on) a designated third party, perhaps one of your competitors. Similarly to the prices of Defensive Licenses, the prices of&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Strategic Licenses also change from Cost Price of Regular Price to Validated Price depending on the stage they are acquired.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"><span style="font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Request to Participate</span> - use this form to </span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">inform SynPat about their intention to participate in the syndicate to crowdfund the SUP. To use it, download and print it, fill it in and exe<gs id="dbd8fc4c-e2d9-4a45-af8b-01a397f0ad1d" ginger_software_uiphraseguid="12c8c73d-7fee-446a-b0ff-22ad333c9919" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark">c</gs>ute it, then use the PARTICIPATE button on the Portfolio page to upload and submit it to SynPat. Please note that your participation fee will be determined according to the formula: Seller''s Asking Price / Number of Participants. &nbsp;The maximum amount that you state on your RTP is for SynPat to figure out whether your request is suffice for participation taking into consideration the Requests to Participate&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">submitted by others. Ultimately, you, like </span><gs id="8a0ee4c8-35f5-4547-bffd-ffe33c526a63" ginger_software_uiphraseguid="17da7684-6538-4634-be21-57f0bc68d8dc" class="GINGER_SOFTWARE_mark" style="line-height: 1.42857;">all</gs><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"> other Participants will pay the same amount: Cost Price = SUP/NoP.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;">Program</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"> - The SynPat Program Procedure and Policies (PPP) describes in details the unique licensing approach offered by SynPat.</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.42857; font-weight: bold;">Download / Upload</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;"> - use this section to download any of the above documents. If you would like to suggest revisions to the language of any of the documents you may do so by downloading them, making your tracked edits and submitting them back to SynPat using the form on this page.</span></div>', '', '', '', '', 2, 'The Syndication stage of this portfolio has completed. At this time, you may acquire a Regular License', 'The Syndication stage for this portfolio is still open, and you may acquire a license as a Participant. Regular Licenses will be available upon a successful syndication.', 'Risk Averse Licenses will be available upon completion of both the Syndication and the Regular Licensing stages.', '<p>Thank you for your interest in participating in this syndicate. Please feel free to contact me with any questions. As you may know, the participation fee is calculated by dividing the Seller''s Upfront Price by the number of Participants. Please download the Request to Participate from the Documents tab, fill it out and submit it to SynPat, using this form.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Regular License under this portfoio. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent Licensee Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and submit it to SynPat using this form. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 50% higher than the price each Participant paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired (as a Strategic License) by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', '<p>Thank you for your interest in aquiring a Validated License under this patent portfoio. We call it a Validated License because so many other licensees have validated this patent portfolio since it was introduced by SynPat. In order to acquire the license, please download the Patent License Agreement from the Documents tab, execute it, and upload it using the button below. SynPat will counter execute the agreement and send it back to you together with an invoice for payment of your license fees, which will be 100% higher than the amount each Regular Licensee paid.</p>\n<p>In the event that your license was already acquired by another operating company, SynPat will inform you about that and will not be able to sell the license to you.</p>', 0, '<div><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Under SynPatâ€™s Open Licensing Program licenses (either Defensive or Strategic) are offered in a non-</span><span style="line-height: 18.5714px;">discriminatory fashion&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">at three prices, depending solely on the time of purchase:</span></div><div><ul><li><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">During the syndication period, licenses are available at a price equal to the Upfront Price divided by the total number of licenses bought by Participants (</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857; font-weight: bold;">â€œCost Priceâ€</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">).</span><br></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Regular Licensing - during the four (4) month period following the Closing, licenses are available at a price equal to 1.5 x Cost Price (</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857; font-weight: bold;">â€œRegular Priceâ€</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">).</span><br></li><li><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">Validated Licensing - thereafter, SynPat still makes licenses at a price equal to twice the Regular Price (</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857; font-weight: bold;">â€œValidated Priceâ€</span><span style="line-height: 1.42857;">). The premium price reflects the market''s acknowledgement of both the patents and the licenses.</span><br></li></ul></div>', '12345', '', 'admin@123', '', '12345', NULL, '', '12345', NULL, '12345', '12345', '', '12345', '', '12345', '', 'admin@123'),
