(164, '', 'Metro_Enterprises', 0, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, '', '2016-06-01', '0.6', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '<p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 15px; line-height: 24px; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);">SynPat decided to acquire this patent portfolio since it covers many potential licensees who could benefit from obtaining licenses that are unavailable otherwise. This portfolio is directed to marketing systems known as "pay-per-call" - </span>mechanisms that allow a telephone lead source to sell the lead to the marketer who is willing to pay the highest price for the lead. &nbsp;M<span style="line-height: 1.6;">arketers bid against one another for a per-call charge. When a lead source receives a telephone call from a customer the telephone call is routed to the highest bidder.&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 1.6;">In case the highest bidder does not answer the call within a predetermined number of rings, the call is re-routed to the next highest bidder, and t</span><span style="line-height: 1.6;">he service provider who answers the call is charged.</span></p><p>Companies that provide services that&nbsp;<span style="line-height: 1.6;">rout customers'' calls to one of many interested marketers based on the price the marketers are interested to pay for the lead may find this opportunity to acquire non-exclusive as well as strategic licenses appealing.</span></p><p><br></p><p>The priority date of this portfolio is December 22, 2004. &nbsp;The portfolio is comprised of three US patents, and several expired Japanese, Canadian, and Australian patents.<br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 15px; line-height: 24px; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 15px; line-height: 24px; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);">The expected number of licensees as they spread along the different segments of the market together with the information provided in this docket support a rational decision to invest and participate in the effort to crowdfund the acquisition of this portfolio, and to acquire non-exclusive and strategic licenses.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 15px; line-height: 24px; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 15px; line-height: 24px; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);">So long as SynPat holds a portfolio of patents, any operating company may submit to SynPat a request to acquire from SynPat either a <span style="font-weight: bold;">Defensive License</span>, a <span style="font-weight: bold;">Strategic License</span>, or both.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 15px; line-height: 24px; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 15px; line-height: 24px; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);">A Defensive License is a paid up nonexclusive license under the acquired patent portfolio. A Strategic License provides its buyer the right to license any other operating company of its choice (â€œDesignated Third Partyâ€).&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 15px; line-height: 24px; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 15px; line-height: 24px; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);"><span style="font-weight: bold;">A request to acquire a license is always subject to availability</span>. &nbsp;For example, a request by Company A to acquire a Strategic License that would allow it to exclusively license Company B must arrive to SynPat before a similar request from Company C, or a request from Company B to acquire a Defensive License is received by SynPat. Also, a request by Company B to acquire a Defensive License must arrive to SynPat before a request from Company A to acquire a Strategic License, which would allow it to exclusively license Company B, is received by SynPat.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 15px; line-height: 24px; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(68, 68, 65); font-size: 15px; line-height: 24px; background-color: rgb(247, 247, 247);">In guiding its actions, SynPat will use the date and time of actual receipt of any request, and unless the date and time of the request to acquire the right to license a Designated Third Party can be clearly shown to have been received by SynPat prior to a request for a Defensive License by the Designated Third Party, SynPat will honor the request of the Designated Third Party.&nbsp;</span></p>', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1, '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, NULL, '12345', '', 'admin@123', '', '12345', NULL, '', '12345', NULL, '12345', '12345', '', '12345', '', '12345', '', 'admin@123');
